WEBVTT

1
00:00:56.900 --> 00:01:00.899
<i>These violent delights
have violent ends...</i>

2
00:01:01.203 --> 00:01:03.479
<i>And in their triumph die...</i>

3
00:01:03.779 --> 00:01:06.146
<i>...like fire and powder.</i>

4
00:01:06.155 --> 00:01:08.563
<i>Which. as they kiss...</i>

5
00:01:08.569 --> 00:01:11.149
<i>...consume.</i>

6
00:01:43.979 --> 00:01:46.107
Gran?

7
00:02:02.052 --> 00:02:04.768
Edward. don't!
She will see you.

8
00:02:14.607 --> 00:02:16.594
Okay.

9
00:02:26.455 --> 00:02:28.516
Grandma. I would like
you to meet...

10
00:02:58.115 --> 00:03:00.719
Happy birthday. Bella.

11
00:03:12.640 --> 00:03:15.143
Happy birthday. Bells.

12
00:03:18.564 --> 00:03:20.799
I thought we agreed.
no presents.

13
00:03:20.840 --> 00:03:24.921
Well. the one from me is not
wrapped. So. it doesn't count.

14
00:03:27.950 --> 00:03:30.941
It's actually great.
Thanks. Dad.

15
00:03:30.975 --> 00:03:33.577
Uh. goes with this one
from your mom.

16
00:03:33.612 --> 00:03:35.436
We coordinated.

17
00:03:35.471 --> 00:03:37.894
Well. she coordinated me.

18
00:03:39.279 --> 00:03:43.431
It's to put your pictures in.
from senior year.

19
00:03:45.197 --> 00:03:47.379
Senior year.

20
00:03:47.415 --> 00:03:49.101
How'd you get so old so fast?

21
00:03:49.136 --> 00:03:51.382
I didn't.
It's not that old.

22
00:03:51.416 --> 00:03:52.647
I don't know.

23
00:03:52.683 --> 00:03:54.021
Is that a grey hair?

24
00:03:54.350 --> 00:03:56.766
No! No way!

25
00:03:59.686 --> 00:04:01.516
Happy Birthday.

26
00:04:01.551 --> 00:04:03.470
It's really funny.

27
00:04:03.504 --> 00:04:07.941
<i>Another missing hiker brings
the total to three presumed dead.</i>

28
00:04:07.976 --> 00:04:10.446
<i>The Rangers are searching
for the killer animal...</i>

29
00:04:18.861 --> 00:04:20.408
Oh. it's Bella.
Bella!

30
00:04:20.608 --> 00:04:22.283
- Hey.
- Hey.

31
00:04:24.490 --> 00:04:26.731
Today is the big day. Bella.

32
00:04:27.095 --> 00:04:29.021
Uh. R and J essay due?

33
00:04:29.022 --> 00:04:30.599
Oh. yeah!

34
00:04:30.600 --> 00:04:32.932
"Wherefore art thou. Bella?"

35
00:04:33.745 --> 00:04:36.281
I wanna take a picture of you guys.
My Mom...

36
00:04:36.315 --> 00:04:39.034
...wants me to put together. like
a scrapbook full of memories.

37
00:04:39.867 --> 00:04:41.853
Oh. of course. yeah.
-I take them. I'm not in them.

38
00:04:41.888 --> 00:04:43.268
No. no. no. come here.

39
00:04:43.303 --> 00:04:44.889
You'll photoshop my nose
if it looks big. right?

40
00:04:44.970 --> 00:04:47.392
Don't worry. I'm in the picture.
No one will be looking at you guys.

41
00:04:47.393 --> 00:04:48.434
It's good.

42
00:04:50.188 --> 00:04:52.587
Oh. good.
Cullen's here.

43
00:04:52.588 --> 00:04:53.629
Yay.

44
00:04:55.242 --> 00:04:57.023
Well. catch you later.

45
00:05:20.265 --> 00:05:21.594
Happy birthday.

46
00:05:21.629 --> 00:05:22.946
Don't remind me.

47
00:05:24.640 --> 00:05:27.156
Bella. your birth is definitely
something to celebrate.

48
00:05:27.181 --> 00:05:29.925
But my aging is not.
- Your aging?

49
00:05:32.413 --> 00:05:35.339
I think 18 is a little young
to start worring about that.

50
00:05:35.383 --> 00:05:36.954
It's one year older than you.

51
00:05:36.989 --> 00:05:39.682
No. it isn't.
I'm a hundred and nine.

52
00:05:39.718 --> 00:05:43.029
Wow! Maybe I should'nt be
dating such an old man.

53
00:05:43.064 --> 00:05:46.930
It's gross!
I should be thoroughly repulsed.

54
00:05:58.422 --> 00:06:00.076
We have to go to class.

55
00:06:00.112 --> 00:06:01.908
Okay.

56
00:06:05.898 --> 00:06:07.386
Wait a second.

57
00:06:08.570 --> 00:06:10.208
Someone wants you.

58
00:06:10.243 --> 00:06:11.288
Bella!

59
00:06:11.289 --> 00:06:17.473
- Jacob!
- I'll leave you to talk.

60
00:06:22.221 --> 00:06:26.999
Hello. biceps! You know. anabolic
steroids are really bad for you.

61
00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:29.321
Well. I'm just filling out. Bella.

62
00:06:29.378 --> 00:06:32.567
You know. wouldn't seem so drastic
if we hung out more.

63
00:06:33.219 --> 00:06:35.077
We should switch schools.

64
00:06:35.111 --> 00:06:36.623
Then you can come hang out
with the pale faces.

65
00:06:36.623 --> 00:06:37.651
I'm alright.

66
00:06:37.687 --> 00:06:39.845
I prefer the Res school's exclusivity.

67
00:06:39.981 --> 00:06:42.815
They let any old rift raft into this place.

68
00:06:42.850 --> 00:06:45.106
I see.
Why are you slumming it?

69
00:06:45.142 --> 00:06:47.550
I was just buying a part for the Rabbit.

70
00:06:47.639 --> 00:06:50.541
You should really come. take a ride.
when it's done.

71
00:06:50.575 --> 00:06:51.822
Is it fast?

72
00:06:51.856 --> 00:06:55.875
Uhm..it's decent.

73
00:06:55.876 --> 00:06:56.918
Okay.
- Okay. good.

74
00:06:59.828 --> 00:07:01.899
Hey. happy birthday.

75
00:07:02.726 --> 00:07:05.168
Your Dad told my Dad.
So...

76
00:07:05.370 --> 00:07:07.033
Yeah. of course. he did.

77
00:07:07.870 --> 00:07:11.267
I saw this the other day and
thought of you.

78
00:07:12.509 --> 00:07:13.834
It catches bad dreams.

79
00:07:15.747 --> 00:07:18.207
Thats kind of perfect.

80
00:07:20.044 --> 00:07:21.312
Thank you.

81
00:07:21.347 --> 00:07:23.246
No problem.

82
00:07:25.616 --> 00:07:27.855
See you soon. Bye.
- Yeah. see you later.

83
00:07:29.316 --> 00:07:32.130
So. how come Jacob Black gets to
give you a gift and I don't?

84
00:07:34.020 --> 00:07:36.287
Because I have nothing
to give back to you.

85
00:07:37.909 --> 00:07:40.368
Bella. you give me everything
just by breathing.

86
00:07:42.665 --> 00:07:45.665
See? Thank you.
That's all I want.

87
00:07:45.801 --> 00:07:46.911
Bella!

88
00:07:48.357 --> 00:07:49.618
Happy Birthday!

89
00:07:49.619 --> 00:07:50.825
Shhh!

90
00:07:53.180 --> 00:07:54.691
Alice. I thought I told you.
no presents.

91
00:07:54.726 --> 00:07:58.263
I've already seen you open it
and guess what? You love it!

92
00:07:58.636 --> 00:08:01.116
You're gonna wear it tonight.
our place.

93
00:08:02.931 --> 00:08:06.749
Come on. please?
It will be fun.

94
00:08:09.558 --> 00:08:11.430
Okay. Alright.

95
00:08:11.465 --> 00:08:13.922
Great! Okay. I'll see you at 7:00.

96
00:08:16.349 --> 00:08:18.051
Jasper...

97
00:08:18.086 --> 00:08:20.449
...no fair with the mood control
thing.

98
00:08:20.752 --> 00:08:22.465
Sorry. Bella.

99
00:08:22.498 --> 00:08:26.100
Happy...
Never mind.

100
00:08:28.493 --> 00:08:30.299
You can't trust vampires.

101
00:08:31.343 --> 00:08:32.522
Trust me!

102
00:08:32.557 --> 00:08:35.379
<i>O. my love!
My wife!</i>

103
00:08:35.414 --> 00:08:38.673
<i>Death that hath sucked
the honey of thy breath.</i>

104
00:08:38.674 --> 00:08:41.340
<i>Hath had no power yet
upon thy beauty.</i>

105
00:08:42.089 --> 00:08:44.170
<i>Thou art not conquered.</i>

106
00:08:45.586 --> 00:08:50.254
<i>Beauty's ensign yet is crimson in thy lips
and in thy cheeks.</i>

107
00:08:50.545 --> 00:08:53.418
<i>And death's pale flag
is not advanced there.</i>

108
00:08:53.668 --> 00:08:55.025
I hate being celebrated.

109
00:08:55.026 --> 00:08:57.763
There are worse tragedies.
Hm. look at Romeo.

110
00:08:57.764 --> 00:09:01.084
He kills his true love
out of sheer stupidity.

111
00:09:02.607 --> 00:09:04.202
Yeah.

112
00:09:04.336 --> 00:09:06.518
Though I do envy him.
one thing.

113
00:09:08.528 --> 00:09:12.891
Juliet. She's like perfect.
If you like that obviously beautiful sort of thing.

114
00:09:17.272 --> 00:09:21.088
No. not the girl. dear.
The suicide.

115
00:09:24.279 --> 00:09:31.478
It's nearly impossible for
some people.

116
00:09:33.155 --> 00:09:38.171
For humans.
a little poison...

117
00:09:38.207 --> 00:09:40.327
...a dagger to the heart...

118
00:09:40.560 --> 00:09:43.817
So many different options.

119
00:09:47.710 --> 00:09:50.018
Why would you say that?

120
00:09:51.132 --> 00:09:53.498
Because I had to considered it once.

121
00:09:55.638 --> 00:09:57.230
I didn't know.
if I'd get to you in time.

122
00:09:58.298 --> 00:10:01.941
I had to come up with
some kind of plan.

123
00:10:03.418 --> 00:10:05.026
And what was the plan?

124
00:10:05.243 --> 00:10:06.779
Uh. go to Italy.

125
00:10:06.814 --> 00:10:08.593
...provoke the Volturi.

126
00:10:08.628 --> 00:10:09.672
The what?

127
00:10:09.808 --> 00:10:11.916
The Volturi.

128
00:10:11.917 --> 00:10:14.451
Now. who would like to repeat
the last few lines...

129
00:10:14.452 --> 00:10:16.743
of iambic pentameter just to show.
they were paying attention?

130
00:10:17.609 --> 00:10:18.648
Mr. Cullen.

131
00:10:21.571 --> 00:10:23.598
Oh. yes. Mr. Birdy. Uhm.

132
00:10:26.102 --> 00:10:29.569
<i>O. here.
Will I set up my everlasting rest.</i>

133
00:10:31.447 --> 00:10:35.159
<i>And shake the yoke of inauspicious stars
from this world-wearied flesh.</i>

134
00:10:35.160 --> 00:10:37.974
<i>Eyes. look your last!</i>

135
00:10:37.975 --> 00:10:40.919
<i>Arms. take your last embrace!</i>

136
00:10:40.920 --> 00:10:45.055
<i>And lips. O you.
the doors of breath.</i>

137
00:10:45.056 --> 00:10:48.039
<i>...seal with a righteous kiss.</i>

138
00:10:48.040 --> 00:10:50.263
<i>A dateless bargain to engrossing death!</i>

139
00:10:52.576 --> 00:10:54.400
Eyes on the screen. people.

140
00:10:56.485 --> 00:10:59.870
<i>Thus with a kiss I die.</i>

141
00:11:01.980 --> 00:11:05.280
The Volturi are a very old.
very powerful family.

142
00:11:05.315 --> 00:11:08.576
I guess. the closest thing to royalty
my world has.

143
00:11:09.009 --> 00:11:11.399
Is that Carlisle?

144
00:11:11.734 --> 00:11:15.576
Yeah. He lived with them
for a few decades.

145
00:11:15.736 --> 00:11:17.916
Described them as
very refined.

146
00:11:17.949 --> 00:11:20.576
No respect for human life.
of course. but...

147
00:11:21.010 --> 00:11:25.049
...respect for the arts
and sciences at least.

148
00:11:25.675 --> 00:11:27.627
<i>And the law...</i>

149
00:11:28.929 --> 00:11:30.658
<i>...above all. the law.</i>

150
00:11:33.848 --> 00:11:35.514
<i>Vampires have laws?</i>

151
00:11:37.214 --> 00:11:38.985
<i>Not very many.</i>

152
00:11:39.970 --> 00:11:42.838
<i>And only one thats
regularly enforced.</i>

153
00:11:44.958 --> 00:11:46.148
<i>What is it?</i>

154
00:11:47.726 --> 00:11:50.911
<i>That we keep the existence
of our kind a secret.</i>

155
00:11:50.947 --> 00:11:54.612
<i>We don't make spectacles
of ourselves.</i>

156
00:11:56.179 --> 00:11:58.849
<i>And we don't kill conspicuously.</i>

157
00:12:02.792 --> 00:12:05.255
<i>Unless. of course.
you want to die.</i>

158
00:12:19.441 --> 00:12:21.233
We have to stop talking
about that.

159
00:12:21.269 --> 00:12:26.019
I can't even think...
...about someone hurting you.

160
00:12:27.660 --> 00:12:32.868
Bella. the only thing that
can hurt me is you.

161
00:12:34.477 --> 00:12:36.666
And I don't have anything else
to be afraid of.

162
00:12:36.701 --> 00:12:38.689
That's not true.

163
00:12:40.413 --> 00:12:42.986
Victoria?
She will come for me one day.

164
00:12:43.953 --> 00:12:48.935
Alice will see
what she decides and...

165
00:12:48.970 --> 00:12:50.716
...we will be ready.
- I can protect you.

166
00:12:52.173 --> 00:12:53.492
If you change me.

167
00:12:54.123 --> 00:12:56.776
Bella. you already do protect me.

168
00:12:58.045 --> 00:13:04.774
You're my only reason
to stay alive.

169
00:13:04.809 --> 00:13:06.507
...if that's what I am.

170
00:13:08.602 --> 00:13:11.115
But it's my job to protect you.

171
00:13:14.549 --> 00:13:16.812
From everyone...

172
00:13:16.846 --> 00:13:18.377
...except my sister.

173
00:13:18.412 --> 00:13:21.255
It's time!
It's time! It's time! It's time!

174
00:13:31.844 --> 00:13:33.352
Sorry about all this.

175
00:13:33.388 --> 00:13:35.302
We tried to rein Alice in.

176
00:13:35.338 --> 00:13:36.714
Like it's even possible.

177
00:13:36.752 --> 00:13:38.435
Happy big Birthday. Bella!

178
00:13:38.436 --> 00:13:39.396
Thanks.

179
00:13:42.433 --> 00:13:44.602
I found it in your bag...

180
00:13:44.637 --> 00:13:45.539
Do you mind?

181
00:13:45.575 --> 00:13:47.498
Dating an older woman?
Hot!

182
00:13:50.110 --> 00:13:51.113
What?

183
00:13:51.114 --> 00:13:52.176
You first Rosalie.

184
00:13:55.076 --> 00:13:58.519
It's a necklace. Alice picked it out.

185
00:13:58.520 --> 00:13:59.894
Thanks.

186
00:14:02.881 --> 00:14:04.776
Show me the love.

187
00:14:07.921 --> 00:14:10.530
This one's from Emmett.

188
00:14:12.403 --> 00:14:14.884
Already installed it in your truck.

189
00:14:15.051 --> 00:14:17.808
Finally. a decent sound system
for that piece of cr...

190
00:14:17.843 --> 00:14:19.861
Hey. don't... don't hate the truck.

191
00:14:19.896 --> 00:14:22.289
Open Esme and Carlisle's.

192
00:14:23.724 --> 00:14:26.344
Just a little something
to brighten your day.

193
00:14:26.379 --> 00:14:28.698
We think. you're looking
kind of pale lately.

194
00:14:33.902 --> 00:14:34.944
Ow.

195
00:14:37.069 --> 00:14:38.833
Paper cut.

196
00:15:03.263 --> 00:15:05.577
Jas... Jas!... shh. shh.
It's okay.

197
00:15:05.639 --> 00:15:09.529
It's just a little...blood.

198
00:15:16.736 --> 00:15:18.922
Get Jasper out of here.

199
00:15:24.236 --> 00:15:27.124
I'm sor...
I'm sorry. I can't.

200
00:15:27.161 --> 00:15:31.225
I'll have to stitch this up
in my office.

201
00:15:33.812 --> 00:15:35.909
Check on Jasper. I'm sure
he's very upset with himself.

202
00:15:35.994 --> 00:15:40.880
And I doubt he'll listen to anyone
but you right now.

203
00:15:41.211 --> 00:15:42.557
Edward.

204
00:15:53.739 --> 00:15:55.850
I never wanted to have a party.

205
00:15:56.184 --> 00:15:58.917
It's not your fault.

206
00:15:59.052 --> 00:16:02.546
Jasper hasn't been away from human blood
as long as the rest of us.

207
00:16:04.063 --> 00:16:06.117
How do you do it?

208
00:16:06.751 --> 00:16:09.406
Years and years of practice.

209
00:16:09.441 --> 00:16:11.606
Did you ever think of...

210
00:16:11.940 --> 00:16:14.462
...just doing it the easier way?

211
00:16:15.145 --> 00:16:19.587
No. I knew who I
wanted to be.

212
00:16:19.722 --> 00:16:23.585
I wanted to help people.
Brings me happiness.

213
00:16:23.720 --> 00:16:25.984
Even if I'm damned about this.

214
00:16:27.723 --> 00:16:33.197
Damned?
Like... like hell?

215
00:16:39.198 --> 00:16:41.390
Carlisle. you can't be damned.

216
00:16:42.213 --> 00:16:44.019
You couldn't. it's impossible.

217
00:16:44.714 --> 00:16:46.495
Thank you. Bella.

218
00:16:46.579 --> 00:16:50.944
You always been very
gracious about us.

219
00:16:54.575 --> 00:16:58.849
So. that's it?
That's why he won't change me?

220
00:17:00.991 --> 00:17:03.381
Imagine the situation in reverse.

221
00:17:05.482 --> 00:17:08.438
If you believed as Edward does

222
00:17:08.473 --> 00:17:11.606
...could you take away his soul?

223
00:17:34.702 --> 00:17:38.164
You can't protect me.

224
00:17:39.074 --> 00:17:40.580
From everything.

225
00:17:40.614 --> 00:17:43.442
At some point.
something's gonna separate us.

226
00:17:45.263 --> 00:17:47.628
It's gonna be an accident.

227
00:17:47.629 --> 00:17:48.753
....or illness.

228
00:17:49.911 --> 00:17:51.294
...or old age.

229
00:17:52.297 --> 00:17:54.399
As long as I'm human.

230
00:17:55.059 --> 00:17:57.669
And the only solution
is to change me.

231
00:17:59.164 --> 00:18:02.352
That's not a solution.
it's a tragedy.

232
00:18:02.386 --> 00:18:04.677
You're not gonna want me
when I look like a grandmother.

233
00:18:14.761 --> 00:18:20.786
Bella. do you not understand
my feelings for you? No?

234
00:18:21.698 --> 00:18:32.250
Carlisle told me how you
feel about your soul.

235
00:18:32.251 --> 00:18:33.294
I don't believe that.

236
00:18:33.292 --> 00:18:35.499
So don't worry about mine.

237
00:18:36.558 --> 00:18:39.081
You should go inside.

238
00:18:52.853 --> 00:18:55.508
It's still my birthday.

239
00:18:58.633 --> 00:19:01.334
Can I ask one thing?

240
00:19:04.063 --> 00:19:07.062
Kiss me?

241
00:19:36.754 --> 00:19:39.043
I love you.

242
00:19:41.255 --> 00:19:42.873
I love you.

243
00:21:03.946 --> 00:21:05.078
Hey.

244
00:21:08.736 --> 00:21:12.255
Come for a walk with me.

245
00:21:34.999 --> 00:21:37.562
We got to leave Forks.

246
00:21:40.437 --> 00:21:42.121
Why?

247
00:21:45.145 --> 00:21:48.099
Carlisle's supposed to be
ten years older than he looks.

248
00:21:48.892 --> 00:21:52.118
People are starting to notice.

249
00:21:53.618 --> 00:21:55.353
Okay.I..

250
00:21:56.117 --> 00:22:00.107
I gotta think of something
to say to Charlie.

251
00:22:09.689 --> 00:22:12.041
When you say "we"...

252
00:22:15.771 --> 00:22:18.523
I mean to my family and myself.

253
00:22:22.181 --> 00:22:26.467
Edward. what happened with Jasper.

254
00:22:26.502 --> 00:22:28.006
...it's nothing.
- You're right.

255
00:22:28.041 --> 00:22:29.851
It was nothing.

256
00:22:31.347 --> 00:22:34.372
Nothing the way
I always expected.

257
00:22:36.762 --> 00:22:39.835
And nothing compared to
what could have happened.

258
00:22:45.321 --> 00:22:48.226
You just don't belong
to my world. Bella.

259
00:22:53.026 --> 00:22:55.584
I belong with you.

260
00:22:57.597 --> 00:22:59.879
No. you don't.

261
00:23:01.285 --> 00:23:02.970
I'm coming.

262
00:23:03.999 --> 00:23:09.122
Bella...
I don't want you to come.

263
00:23:16.348 --> 00:23:19.524
You don't want me?

264
00:23:23.777 --> 00:23:25.610
No.

265
00:23:28.677 --> 00:23:32.973
This changes things...a lot.

266
00:23:33.598 --> 00:23:35.308
But if it's not
too much to ask...

267
00:23:37.787 --> 00:23:40.467
...can you at least
promise me something?

268
00:23:42.697 --> 00:23:44.803
Don't do anything reckless.

269
00:23:47.529 --> 00:23:49.618
For Charlie's sake.

270
00:23:50.872 --> 00:23:53.377
And I'll promise something
to you in return.

271
00:23:53.607 --> 00:23:56.574
This is the last time
you'll ever see me.

272
00:23:57.387 --> 00:23:59.111
I won't come back.

273
00:23:59.144 --> 00:24:01.552
And you can go on
with your life...

274
00:24:01.553 --> 00:24:03.009
...without any interference from me.

275
00:24:03.848 --> 00:24:08.321
It will be like I never existed.
I promise.

276
00:24:11.178 --> 00:24:13.674
If this is about my soul. take it.

277
00:24:13.675 --> 00:24:14.633
I don't want it without you.

278
00:24:15.333 --> 00:24:17.828
It's not about your soul.

279
00:24:20.088 --> 00:24:23.733
You're just not good for me.

280
00:24:24.349 --> 00:24:26.459
I'm not good enough for you?

281
00:24:27.093 --> 00:24:30.489
I'm just sorry.
I let this go on for so long.

282
00:24:31.721 --> 00:24:34.192
Please...

283
00:24:34.759 --> 00:24:36.059
...don't.

284
00:24:41.299 --> 00:24:43.920
Goodbye.

285
00:24:58.689 --> 00:25:00.489
Edward?

286
00:25:12.204 --> 00:25:13.299
Edward!

287
00:25:17.764 --> 00:25:18.804
Edward!

288
00:25:22.136 --> 00:25:23.524
Edward?

289
00:25:31.542 --> 00:25:32.583
Edward.

290
00:27:27.891 --> 00:27:30.053
I'll try to call Cullens place again.

291
00:27:31.191 --> 00:27:33.442
The Cullens left town. Charlie.

292
00:27:33.477 --> 00:27:34.525
Good riddance!

293
00:27:34.560 --> 00:27:36.021
Where did they go?

294
00:27:37.007 --> 00:27:39.088
We'll find her. Charlie.

295
00:27:39.124 --> 00:27:40.835
Thanks. Harry.

296
00:27:40.869 --> 00:27:41.941
Charlie!

297
00:27:45.865 --> 00:27:47.660
She's alright.

298
00:27:48.768 --> 00:27:50.298
I got her.

299
00:27:51.045 --> 00:27:52.415
Thank you. Sam.

300
00:28:18.516 --> 00:28:22.584
October.

301
00:28:47.033 --> 00:28:51.131
November.

302
00:29:01.877 --> 00:29:06.005
<i>Alice... ...you've disappeared.</i>

303
00:29:08.215 --> 00:29:09.824
<i>Like everything else.</i>

304
00:29:11.085 --> 00:29:14.319
<i>But who else can I talk to?
I'm lost.</i>

305
00:29:16.505 --> 00:29:20.840
December.

306
00:29:20.975 --> 00:29:22.942
<i>When you left...</i>

307
00:29:25.008 --> 00:29:26.460
<i>and he left...</i>

308
00:29:28.207 --> 00:29:30.921
<i>You took everything with you.</i>

309
00:29:33.061 --> 00:29:35.636
<i>But the absence of him
is everywhere I look...</i>

310
00:29:43.258 --> 00:29:47.736
<i>It's like a huge hole has been
punched through my chest.</i>

311
00:30:09.790 --> 00:30:11.558
<i>But in a way I'm glad.</i>

312
00:30:12.289 --> 00:30:15.183
<i>The pain is my only reminder that
he was real...</i>

313
00:30:15.281 --> 00:30:17.745
<i>...that you all were.</i>

314
00:30:18.641 --> 00:30:21.620
<i>"Undelivered Mail Returned to Sender"</i>

315
00:30:25.635 --> 00:30:28.427
Alright. that's it.

316
00:30:30.809 --> 00:30:32.155
What?

317
00:30:32.191 --> 00:30:33.711
You're going to Jacksonville

318
00:30:33.745 --> 00:30:35.477
...to live with your mother.

319
00:30:37.792 --> 00:30:39.987
I'm not leaving Forks.

320
00:30:40.906 --> 00:30:46.612
Bells. he's not coming back.

321
00:30:48.106 --> 00:30:49.911
I know.

322
00:30:50.753 --> 00:30:53.941
It's just not normal.
this behavior.

323
00:30:53.975 --> 00:30:58.030
Quite frankly. it's scaring
the hell outta me and your Mother.

324
00:30:59.311 --> 00:31:02.655
Baby. I... I don't want you to leave.

325
00:31:03.554 --> 00:31:06.109
Go to Jacksonville.

326
00:31:06.143 --> 00:31:07.258
...make some new friends.

327
00:31:07.291 --> 00:31:08.909
I like my old friends.

328
00:31:08.944 --> 00:31:10.624
Well. you never see them anymore.

329
00:31:10.660 --> 00:31:12.645
I do. yeah.

330
00:31:16.972 --> 00:31:20.240
I'm gonna go shopping tomorrow.
with Jessica.

331
00:31:21.349 --> 00:31:22.886
You hate shopping.

332
00:31:23.321 --> 00:31:27.617
I need a girl's night out.

333
00:31:29.886 --> 00:31:32.874
Alright.
Girl's night.

334
00:31:33.874 --> 00:31:35.839
Shopping.

335
00:31:36.039 --> 00:31:41.158
I like it. go.
Buy some good stuff.

336
00:31:48.376 --> 00:31:50.185
<i>Hi. Jessica. it's Bella.</i>

337
00:31:51.018 --> 00:31:53.510
<i>Oh. yeah. Bella Swan.</i>

338
00:31:58.540 --> 00:32:01.460
I don't know. why you wanna sit through
all those zombies eating people.

339
00:32:01.860 --> 00:32:04.759
...and no hot guys kissing anybody.
It's gross.

340
00:32:05.190 --> 00:32:07.233
Like why there are
so many zombie movies anyway?.

341
00:32:07.330 --> 00:32:09.354
Is it supposed to like
draw a parallel about leprosy?

342
00:32:09.653 --> 00:32:12.102
My cousin had leprosy.
it's not funny. you know?

343
00:32:13.573 --> 00:32:16.337
And like is it supposed to be
a metaphor for consumerism?

344
00:32:16.338 --> 00:32:20.141
Cause don't be so pleased with your own
like. self-reverential cleverness. you know?

345
00:32:21.072 --> 00:32:24.044
Like. some girls like to shop.
Not all girls. apparently.

346
00:32:24.136 --> 00:32:26.288
Although I was surprised you
even called at all. you know?

347
00:32:26.787 --> 00:32:30.436
Like. your depression thing.
I get it. I'm totally totally worried.

348
00:32:30.637 --> 00:32:33.044
After a while. it's like.
she's still bumming?

349
00:32:33.107 --> 00:32:34.878
And I'm going through
stuff too. you know?

350
00:32:35.263 --> 00:32:37.651
Like Mike deciding
he wanted to "just be friends"!

351
00:32:37.985 --> 00:32:39.888
It's hard. you know?

352
00:32:39.889 --> 00:32:40.931
<i>What's up. guys?</i>

353
00:32:40.932 --> 00:32:41.973
<i>Where you going?</i>

354
00:32:51.549 --> 00:32:53.001
<i>Keep walking.</i>

355
00:32:54.603 --> 00:32:57.392
<i>This is dangerous.</i>

356
00:33:05.603 --> 00:33:07.212
Dude. come on.

357
00:33:07.213 --> 00:33:08.254
<i>Come here for a sec!</i>

358
00:33:12.458 --> 00:33:14.910
I think. I know those guys.

359
00:33:14.911 --> 00:33:16.608
<i>We got beer! We got bikes!</i>

360
00:33:18.503 --> 00:33:20.736
Well. they seem great.
Can we go?

361
00:33:21.692 --> 00:33:23.318
I just need to see something.

362
00:33:25.402 --> 00:33:26.444
<i>Hey. girlie!</i>

363
00:33:30.711 --> 00:33:33.061
Alright. Alright!
We got a taker.

364
00:33:34.244 --> 00:33:35.719
<i>Turn around.</i>

365
00:33:50.294 --> 00:33:51.335
<i>Shut up! Shut up!</i>

366
00:33:58.817 --> 00:34:00.533
Sorry. I thought
you were somebody else.

367
00:34:00.768 --> 00:34:03.224
That's cool! I'll be whomever
you want to be. honey.

368
00:34:03.588 --> 00:34:06.790
So. what do you say?

369
00:34:10.399 --> 00:34:12.762
<i>You promised me nothing reckless.</i>

370
00:34:16.947 --> 00:34:20.621
You promised. it would as
if you never existed.

371
00:34:25.336 --> 00:34:26.991
You lied.

372
00:34:26.991 --> 00:34:30.353
Say some'n. babe?
You know what? Never mind.

373
00:34:46.813 --> 00:34:47.864
Stop.

374
00:34:48.165 --> 00:34:50.217
Stop! Stop! Stop!

375
00:35:00.751 --> 00:35:04.159
Hey. um. what the hell is wrong with you?
-Just curious.

376
00:35:06.004 --> 00:35:07.302
I thought that I saw something.

377
00:35:08.734 --> 00:35:12.220
You're insane. actually.
Or suicidal.

378
00:35:12.623 --> 00:35:15.334
That homeboy
could have been a psycho.

379
00:35:15.334 --> 00:35:19.812
I was about to end up in a FBI interview
room.like some lame TV show.

380
00:35:20.709 --> 00:35:24.265
That was such a rush!
-Awesome!

381
00:35:24.300 --> 00:35:26.962
So. you're an adrenaline junky now?

382
00:35:27.000 --> 00:35:28.611
That's cool!
You can go bungee jumping.

383
00:35:28.612 --> 00:35:31.138
You don't get on the back of some
random loser's motorcycle!

384
00:35:31.139 --> 00:35:32.365
Crazy!

385
00:35:37.089 --> 00:35:39.566
<i>Alice. I saw him.</i>

386
00:35:41.498 --> 00:35:44.122
<i>Maybe I'm crazy now.
but I guess that's okay.</i>

387
00:35:46.731 --> 00:35:51.439
<i>If a rush of danger is what it takes
to see him. then that's what I'll find.</i>

388
00:35:55.604 --> 00:35:56.645
Bella!

389
00:35:58.479 --> 00:36:00.603
Where the hell have you been. looker?

390
00:36:06.062 --> 00:36:07.552
I... brought you something.
- Okay.

391
00:36:09.209 --> 00:36:10.554
It's a little crazy.

392
00:36:16.590 --> 00:36:18.837
Wow. scrap metal!
You shouldn't have.

393
00:36:18.871 --> 00:36:21.858
I saved it from the junkyard.

394
00:36:23.526 --> 00:36:26.236
I think. they'll probably cost
more to fix than they're worth..

395
00:36:27.411 --> 00:36:30.946
But then I thought that if I had a
mechanic friend to help me out.

396
00:36:31.473 --> 00:36:35.249
Ah! Me. being the mechanic-type friend?
- That's right.

397
00:36:35.806 --> 00:36:37.984
Since when are you into motorcycles?

398
00:36:38.020 --> 00:36:39.367
Since now.

399
00:36:44.020 --> 00:36:48.437
I get it if you think that this
is really stupid and reckless.

400
00:36:48.472 --> 00:36:51.175
Yeah. it's completely
stupid and reckless.

401
00:36:54.255 --> 00:36:56.200
When do we start?

402
00:37:00.057 --> 00:37:01.663
Now!

403
00:37:01.999 --> 00:37:04.283
Please.
- Alright.

404
00:37:06.451 --> 00:37:10.063
Oh. hey. be careful. These things
are actually really...heavy. So.

405
00:37:15.676 --> 00:37:20.419
Jake. you're like buff. How that can happen?
You're like 16. I don't get it.

406
00:37:21.220 --> 00:37:24.835
Age is just a number. baby.
What. you're like 40. now?

407
00:37:28.350 --> 00:37:29.735
Feels like that sometimes.

408
00:37:40.879 --> 00:37:43.552
That song was good.
You don't like it?

409
00:37:44.598 --> 00:37:47.982
I don't really like music anymore

410
00:37:48.283 --> 00:37:51.078
...kind of.
- Okay.

411
00:37:51.280 --> 00:37:53.208
No more music.

412
00:37:55.476 --> 00:37:58.755
I was thinking.if we're gonna do this
everyday. and hopefully we will.

413
00:37:59.240 --> 00:38:02.250
We have to. like. fit some
homework in there somewhere.

414
00:38:02.286 --> 00:38:04.741
I don't want Billy thinking that
I'm a bad influence on you.

415
00:38:05.576 --> 00:38:07.349
You influence me?

416
00:38:07.884 --> 00:38:08.966
Please.

417
00:38:11.578 --> 00:38:13.400
Are you...?
I'm older than you.

418
00:38:13.401 --> 00:38:16.724
So that makes me the influencer
and you the influence.

419
00:38:16.759 --> 00:38:22.525
No. no. no. My size and knowledge base
actually makes me older than you.

420
00:38:22.626 --> 00:38:24.706
Because of your gentle paleness
and lack of know-how.

421
00:38:24.840 --> 00:38:27.118
I convinced you to build
two-wheeled death machines with me.

422
00:38:27.585 --> 00:38:29.797
Don't you think that makes
you funny. young and naive?

423
00:38:30.989 --> 00:38:33.572
Okay.
So. where do we stand?

424
00:38:34.134 --> 00:38:35.756
I'm thirty five...

425
00:38:35.959 --> 00:38:37.462
...and you might be like 32.

426
00:38:37.698 --> 00:38:38.617
Come on.

427
00:38:38.650 --> 00:38:39.577
Yo. Jake. you in there?
- No. it's okay.

428
00:38:41.287 --> 00:38:42.799
It's... It's just my boys.

429
00:38:42.835 --> 00:38:43.854
Hey. Jake...

430
00:38:43.889 --> 00:38:45.866
Hey. Guys. this is Bella.

431
00:38:45.901 --> 00:38:48.275
Bella. that's Quil and Embry.

432
00:38:48.276 --> 00:38:50.698
I'm Quil Ateara.

433
00:38:52.206 --> 00:38:54.257
So the bike building story is true.

434
00:38:54.358 --> 00:38:56.713
Oh. yeah. yeah!
I taught him everything he knows.

435
00:38:56.748 --> 00:38:59.617
What about the part
where you're his girlfriend?

436
00:39:00.915 --> 00:39:02.162
Uh. we're friends. you know?

437
00:39:02.295 --> 00:39:03.753
Hmm. Burn!

438
00:39:04.879 --> 00:39:07.715
Actually. I remember. I said
she's a girl and a friend.

439
00:39:07.751 --> 00:39:09.563
Embry. do you remember him
making that distinction?

440
00:39:09.699 --> 00:39:10.489
Nope!

441
00:39:10.525 --> 00:39:12.888
So you guys have girlfriends.
It's awesome.

442
00:39:14.340 --> 00:39:15.493
Yeah. right.

443
00:39:15.728 --> 00:39:17.879
Quil's actually taken his cousin to prom.

444
00:39:18.813 --> 00:39:20.253
Yeah. that's still a riot.

445
00:39:20.288 --> 00:39:22.188
You want funny. Black?
I'll give you funny.

446
00:39:24.271 --> 00:39:25.312
Jesus!

447
00:39:27.389 --> 00:39:29.097
I got five bucks on Quil.

448
00:39:29.331 --> 00:39:30.698
You're on.

449
00:39:53.181 --> 00:39:56.278
<i>Dear Alice. I wish.
I had your real address.</i>

450
00:39:57.363 --> 00:40:00.201
<i>I wish. I could tell you
about Jake.</i>

451
00:40:00.337 --> 00:40:03.544
<i>He makes me feel better..</i>

452
00:40:04.145 --> 00:40:07.533
<i>I mean.
he makes me feel alive.</i>

453
00:40:08.740 --> 00:40:10.240
<i>The hole in my chest...</i>

454
00:40:11.411 --> 00:40:13.946
<i>...while when I'm with Jake.</i>

455
00:40:14.449 --> 00:40:16.785
<i>It's like. it almost healed.</i>

456
00:40:16.786 --> 00:40:18.500
<i>For a while.</i>

457
00:40:18.934 --> 00:40:21.041
Quil keeps asking to come over.

458
00:40:21.076 --> 00:40:22.936
I think he likes you
a little too much.

459
00:40:25.401 --> 00:40:28.223
Oh. I'm really not into
the whole cougar thing. you know?

460
00:40:31.216 --> 00:40:33.093
What's up with you and age?

461
00:40:33.960 --> 00:40:37.428
I mean. how old was that
Cullen guy anyway?

462
00:40:39.216 --> 00:40:41.511
<i>But even Jake can't keep
the dreams away.</i>

463
00:40:53.949 --> 00:40:57.447
Hey. Bella!  Shh. Shh. Shh.
you're alright. You're okay.

464
00:41:08.429 --> 00:41:10.507
I thought this thing was
starting to work.

465
00:41:10.508 --> 00:41:13.699
...but I guess not.

466
00:41:19.109 --> 00:41:21.080
Can I ask you something?

467
00:41:22.665 --> 00:41:25.740
Hanging out with Jacob...

468
00:41:25.816 --> 00:41:29.172
...that seems to take your mind
off things for a bit. doesn't it?

469
00:41:34.518 --> 00:41:40.646
You know. sometimes you gotta
learn to love what's good for you.

470
00:41:42.501 --> 00:41:43.811
You know. what I mean?

471
00:41:46.500 --> 00:41:47.957
Of course. what do I know?

472
00:41:48.903 --> 00:41:51.496
I'm just a terminal bachelor.

473
00:41:53.690 --> 00:41:55.659
Famous ladies man.

474
00:41:58.058 --> 00:42:00.666
Okay...

475
00:42:01.234 --> 00:42:03.438
Go to bed.

476
00:42:05.027 --> 00:42:06.322
I love you.

477
00:42:12.661 --> 00:42:17.212
If I told you. I couldn't fix these
bikes. what would you have said?

478
00:42:19.492 --> 00:42:22.025
Are you doubting your mad skills?

479
00:42:22.689 --> 00:42:23.551
No.

480
00:42:23.552 --> 00:42:26.699
No. definitely not.
I mean. they'll run fine.

481
00:42:26.933 --> 00:42:28.769
It's just. uh...

482
00:42:30.242 --> 00:42:34.101
May be if I was smarter I would've
dragged out the rebuild a bit.

483
00:42:37.764 --> 00:42:43.356
If you told me. you couldn't fix these
bikes. I would say that that's...

484
00:42:43.358 --> 00:42:47.554
...really too bad but were gonna
find something else to do.

485
00:42:52.135 --> 00:42:53.585
Is that Sam Uley?

486
00:42:53.620 --> 00:42:57.087
Yeah. and his cult.

487
00:43:00.574 --> 00:43:04.524
Oh. my God!

488
00:43:04.924 --> 00:43:06.624
Did you see that?

489
00:43:12.628 --> 00:43:14.754
They're not really fighting. Bella.

490
00:43:14.789 --> 00:43:16.574
They're cliff diving.

491
00:43:16.608 --> 00:43:19.511
Scary as hell.
but a total rush

492
00:43:21.980 --> 00:43:23.048
Rush?

493
00:43:23.082 --> 00:43:24.523
Most of us jump from lower down.

494
00:43:24.957 --> 00:43:28.365
We'll leave the showing off
to Sam and his disciples.

495
00:43:30.425 --> 00:43:32.954
Is some kind of beef
with them or something?

496
00:43:34.740 --> 00:43:36.502
Oh. no.

497
00:43:36.538 --> 00:43:38.915
They just think they run this place.

498
00:43:38.949 --> 00:43:43.502
Embry used to call them hall
monitors on steroids.

499
00:43:43.991 --> 00:43:47.630
Now. look at him.
- That's Embry?

500
00:43:47.666 --> 00:43:49.090
Yeah.
- What happened to him?

501
00:43:49.326 --> 00:43:51.340
He missed some school...

502
00:43:51.376 --> 00:43:55.069
...and all of a sudden started following
Sam around like a little puppy.

503
00:43:55.383 --> 00:43:57.816
Same thing with Paul and Jared.

504
00:43:58.550 --> 00:44:05.664
Sam keeps giving me this look. like
he's been waiting for me or something.

505
00:44:06.979 --> 00:44:09.757
It's kinda starting to freak me out.

506
00:44:09.790 --> 00:44:11.962
Well. you should just avoid him.

507
00:44:13.978 --> 00:44:16.540
I'll try.

508
00:44:32.159 --> 00:44:33.198
Okay.

509
00:44:36.807 --> 00:44:38.849
You look scared.
- I'm not.

510
00:44:40.729 --> 00:44:41.644
Alright!

511
00:44:42.164 --> 00:44:44.123
Brake.

512
00:44:47.144 --> 00:44:49.940
Clutch. Good.

513
00:44:49.976 --> 00:44:51.581
Gas.

514
00:44:53.771 --> 00:44:55.162
Ready?

515
00:44:56.162 --> 00:44:58.728
Now slowly... release the clutch.

516
00:45:01.327 --> 00:45:03.575
<i>Bella</i>

517
00:45:06.256 --> 00:45:07.311
<i>Stop.</i>

518
00:45:12.489 --> 00:45:14.017
You alright?

519
00:45:15.418 --> 00:45:17.047
I'm gonna go again.

520
00:45:37.259 --> 00:45:38.662
Hit the brake!

521
00:45:53.335 --> 00:45:54.551
I wanna go again.

522
00:45:54.587 --> 00:45:56.082
Are you trying to get yourself killed?

523
00:45:56.083 --> 00:45:58.801
I'll try again.
- No. forget it.

524
00:45:59.704 --> 00:46:02.046
No more bikes.

525
00:46:02.305 --> 00:46:05.398
Man. your head.

526
00:46:07.559 --> 00:46:09.377
Oh. my God. I'm sorry.

527
00:46:10.239 --> 00:46:12.868
You're apologizing for bleeding?

528
00:46:15.317 --> 00:46:17.077
Yeah. I guess. I am.

529
00:46:17.858 --> 00:46:19.817
Well. it's just blood. Bella.

530
00:46:19.818 --> 00:46:21.784
No big deal.

531
00:46:33.992 --> 00:46:35.558
What are you staring at?

532
00:46:39.398 --> 00:46:41.981
You're sort of beautiful.

533
00:46:49.221 --> 00:46:51.789
How hard did you hit your head?

534
00:46:51.790 --> 00:46:52.831
I dont know.

535
00:46:56.676 --> 00:46:58.542
Let's go.

536
00:47:02.057 --> 00:47:04.855
I did see something.
- Totally. baby. I believe you.

537
00:47:04.890 --> 00:47:07.978
No. he doesn't.
He's just trying to get lucky.

538
00:47:10.128 --> 00:47:12.451
It was jet black and huge.

539
00:47:12.585 --> 00:47:14.734
On all fours. it was still taller
than a person.

540
00:47:14.735 --> 00:47:16.647
A bear. maybe?

541
00:47:16.648 --> 00:47:19.617
Or an alien.
You're lucky that you didn't get probed.

542
00:47:22.091 --> 00:47:23.013
Oh. yeah.
- Well. I saw it.

543
00:47:23.314 --> 00:47:25.110
You're not the only one.

544
00:47:26.273 --> 00:47:28.535
My Dad's been getting
reports at the station.

545
00:47:28.935 --> 00:47:31.545
Like five hikers been killed by some bear.

546
00:47:31.946 --> 00:47:34.205
But they can't find the bear.

547
00:47:37.525 --> 00:47:40.568
Last time you clowns
doubt my girlfriend.

548
00:47:44.148 --> 00:47:47.574
So. I mean...
Bella is back!

549
00:47:51.765 --> 00:47:53.886
Yeah. I guess so.

550
00:47:53.887 --> 00:47:55.680
Huh. that's cool...
Welcome.

551
00:47:57.113 --> 00:48:00.809
So listen. not now that...
You know. you're talking and...

552
00:48:01.310 --> 00:48:02.868
...eating again. you know?

553
00:48:02.969 --> 00:48:06.953
You gotta get that protein in there.

554
00:48:08.457 --> 00:48:12.719
I was just wondering.
if you wanted to go see a movie with me.

555
00:48:16.651 --> 00:48:18.184
Yeah. sure.

556
00:48:18.384 --> 00:48:19.798
Yeah. I do.

557
00:48:21.255 --> 00:48:27.917
Cool. um. let me see...We could check out
"Love Spelled Backwards Is Love".

558
00:48:27.918 --> 00:48:29.945
Yeah. it's a dumb title.

559
00:48:29.946 --> 00:48:32.371
...but. um. it's a romantic comedy.
I mean. it's supposed to be.

560
00:48:32.372 --> 00:48:35.316
No. No romance.

561
00:48:37.617 --> 00:48:41.006
How about "Face Punch"?
You heard of that?

562
00:48:41.007 --> 00:48:45.540
Well. it's an action movie.
- Yeah. it's perfect.

563
00:48:47.074 --> 00:48:50.504
With guns... adrenaline...
...it's my thing

564
00:48:51.004 --> 00:48:52.127
Okay.

565
00:48:52.227 --> 00:48:55.797
We should get a bunch of people to go.
Do you guys wanna go see...

566
00:48:55.900 --> 00:48:58.360
..."Face Punch"?
- "Face Punch"? Yeah!

567
00:48:58.394 --> 00:49:00.879
Mike. hey. we were supposed
to watch that?

568
00:49:00.880 --> 00:49:02.993
Remember the trailer's like punch faces...
- Yeah?

569
00:49:04.726 --> 00:49:06.627
Movie night with Bella!

570
00:49:09.703 --> 00:49:12.969
So. "Face Punch". huh?
You like action movies?

571
00:49:15.067 --> 00:49:17.435
Not really.

572
00:49:19.518 --> 00:49:22.910
I heard it sucks. Bad.

573
00:49:23.709 --> 00:49:26.425
Hey. are you even old enough
to see this movie?

574
00:49:27.633 --> 00:49:29.414
I mean. you know. without adult supervision?
- Right. yeah.

575
00:49:29.714 --> 00:49:32.742
Well. she's buying my ticket for me.
- She's buying it. okay.

576
00:49:34.965 --> 00:49:36.126
Jessica bailed

577
00:49:36.161 --> 00:49:39.484
...and Angela's got the stomach flu.
so Eric's taking care of her.

578
00:49:40.775 --> 00:49:42.730
So. it's just us three.
- Great.

579
00:49:44.197 --> 00:49:45.479
Great.
- Yeah.

580
00:49:48.677 --> 00:49:50.276
<i>Put the gun down.</i>

581
00:49:50.276 --> 00:49:53.150
<i>Put your gun down or I'm gonna
blow your freaking head off.</i>

582
00:49:53.150 --> 00:49:58.702
<i>Put both of your guns down or I'm gonna
blow both of your freaking heads off.</i>

583
00:50:00.460 --> 00:50:03.178
<i>Alright. let's do this!</i>

584
00:50:19.995 --> 00:50:22.789
Okay. I think I'm gonna throw up!

585
00:50:28.342 --> 00:50:32.098
Jesus!
- What a marshmallow!

586
00:50:33.135 --> 00:50:36.052
You should hold out for someone
with a stronger stomach.

587
00:50:36.331 --> 00:50:39.847
Someone who laughs at the gore
that makes weaker men vomit.

588
00:50:39.847 --> 00:50:43.201
Yeah. I'll keep my eye open for that.

589
00:50:43.700 --> 00:50:47.537
I feel bad. He probably has
that flu that's going around.

590
00:50:51.349 --> 00:50:55.744
What? I can't hold your hand?
- No. of course. you can.

591
00:50:59.019 --> 00:51:03.017
I just think it means
something really different to you.

592
00:51:04.892 --> 00:51:09.047
Okay. tell me something.
You like me. right?

593
00:51:13.319 --> 00:51:16.997
And you think. I'm sorta beautiful?

594
00:51:17.017 --> 00:51:21.529
Jake. please...
don't do this.

595
00:51:27.300 --> 00:51:28.898
Why?

596
00:51:31.856 --> 00:51:35.490
Because you are about
to ruin everything.

597
00:51:36.609 --> 00:51:41.242
And I need you.

598
00:51:45.917 --> 00:51:48.951
Well. I've got loads of time.

599
00:51:49.629 --> 00:51:52.745
I'm not gonna give up.

600
00:51:52.745 --> 00:51:55.461
I don't want you to.
- But...

601
00:51:57.378 --> 00:52:01.253
It's just because I don't want you
to go anywhere.

602
00:52:03.689 --> 00:52:07.005
It's... it's really selfish.

603
00:52:09.082 --> 00:52:13.119
You know. I'm not like a car
that you can fix up.

604
00:52:16.553 --> 00:52:18.390
I'm never gonna run right.

605
00:52:18.552 --> 00:52:22.185
So I should be fair to you.

606
00:52:22.825 --> 00:52:26.419
It's because of him. right?

607
00:52:35.368 --> 00:52:40.679
Look. I know what he did to you.

608
00:52:42.038 --> 00:52:47.511
But. Bella. I would never.
ever do that.

609
00:52:48.907 --> 00:52:53.381
I won't ever hurt you.
I promise.

610
00:52:53.381 --> 00:52:56.340
I won't let you down.

611
00:52:56.439 --> 00:52:58.355
You can count on me.

612
00:53:06.325 --> 00:53:08.080
Well...

613
00:53:12.556 --> 00:53:15.671
I need to go home.

614
00:53:20.963 --> 00:53:24.962
I'm... I was feeling sick
before the movie. okay?

615
00:53:27.537 --> 00:53:28.894
What is your problem?

616
00:53:28.894 --> 00:53:31.092
Right now?
You are my problem.

617
00:53:31.491 --> 00:53:36.143
Feeling sick?
Maybe you need to go to the hospital.

618
00:53:36.402 --> 00:53:38.241
Do you want me
to put you in the hospital?

619
00:53:38.320 --> 00:53:42.217
Jake... Jake. the movie's over.
What are you doing?

620
00:53:42.257 --> 00:53:46.390
Jake. you're really hot.

621
00:53:46.490 --> 00:53:49.607
Like. you feel like you have a fever.
Are you okay?

622
00:53:50.463 --> 00:53:53.578
I don't know what's happening.

623
00:53:54.579 --> 00:53:57.414
I gotta go.

624
00:54:01.450 --> 00:54:03.766
That dude is weird.

625
00:54:06.720 --> 00:54:10.037
<i>Jake. Uh. your Dad says you have mono.</i>

626
00:54:10.037 --> 00:54:13.912
<i>He won't let me visit but...
would you call me?</i>

627
00:54:18.746 --> 00:54:24.779
<i>Hey. uh. it's me again. I just...I'm sorry
about what I said at the movie theatre.</i>

628
00:54:26.613 --> 00:54:31.168
<i>I just wanted to hear your voice.
So. no pressure.</i>

629
00:54:32.405 --> 00:54:37.601
Jacob. please call me.

630
00:54:37.640 --> 00:54:41.434
Okay. we should be
back around three.

631
00:54:49.142 --> 00:54:53.018
Look. I don't have to go fishing today.
- Yes. you do.

632
00:54:52.675 --> 00:54:55.511
Yeah. you do. Go.
What are you talking about?

633
00:54:55.550 --> 00:54:58.711
Just be careful.
- I always am.

634
00:55:00.150 --> 00:55:02.588
Those bears won't get
the drop on me. Bella.

635
00:55:02.588 --> 00:55:06.107
My kung foo is strong.

636
00:55:37.698 --> 00:55:40.215
Jake!

637
00:55:46.174 --> 00:55:48.452
You cut your hair off?

638
00:55:51.094 --> 00:55:54.732
And got a tattoo?

639
00:55:56.052 --> 00:55:57.572
Bella...

640
00:55:57.572 --> 00:56:00.209
I thought you were too sick
to come outside.

641
00:56:01.168 --> 00:56:04.570
Or pick up the phone
when I'd call.

642
00:56:05.290 --> 00:56:09.406
Go away.
- What?

643
00:56:10.684 --> 00:56:12.606
Go away.

644
00:56:13.846 --> 00:56:16.442
What happened to you?
What's wrong?

645
00:56:16.442 --> 00:56:19.203
Hey. what happened?

646
00:56:21.683 --> 00:56:24.881
Did Sam get to you?
Is that what's happening?

647
00:56:24.881 --> 00:56:29.121
Sam's trying to help me.
don't blame him.

648
00:56:29.161 --> 00:56:31.719
But if you want somebody to blame.

649
00:56:31.719 --> 00:56:35.779
How about those
filthy bloodsuckers. you love?

650
00:56:35.780 --> 00:56:36.820
The Cullens.

651
00:56:42.876 --> 00:56:46.714
I don't know what are you talking about.
- You know exactly what I'm talking about.

652
00:56:46.835 --> 00:56:50.395
You been lying to everyone.
Charlie...

653
00:56:51.872 --> 00:56:54.311
But you can't lie to me.

654
00:56:55.112 --> 00:56:59.908
Not anymore. Bella.
- Come on! Jacob!

655
00:57:05.070 --> 00:57:06.988
Look. Bella...

656
00:57:07.908 --> 00:57:10.787
We can't be friends anymore.

657
00:57:11.267 --> 00:57:15.784
Jake. I know that I have
been hurting you.

658
00:57:16.826 --> 00:57:20.702
It's... it's killing me.
It kills me.

659
00:57:22.101 --> 00:57:25.463
If you. may be.
give me like some time.

660
00:57:25.463 --> 00:57:26.942
Don't!

661
00:57:27.740 --> 00:57:29.779
It's not you.

662
00:57:32.180 --> 00:57:35.698
It's not you. it's me. right?
Really?

663
00:57:36.138 --> 00:57:39.216
It's true!
It is me.

664
00:57:41.137 --> 00:57:44.535
I'm not... good.

665
00:57:46.255 --> 00:57:49.812
I used to be... a good kid.

666
00:57:50.614 --> 00:57:53.053
Not anymore.

667
00:57:53.213 --> 00:57:57.249
This doesn't even matter. alright?
This is over.

668
00:57:57.249 --> 00:57:59.809
You can't break up with me.

669
00:58:01.409 --> 00:58:03.449
I mean...

670
00:58:04.207 --> 00:58:06.886
I mean. you're my best friend.

671
00:58:08.726 --> 00:58:11.124
You promised me.

672
00:58:11.924 --> 00:58:17.286
I know. I promised I
would'nt hurt you. Bella.

673
00:58:17.765 --> 00:58:20.803
And this is me keeping
that promise. Bella.

674
00:58:20.923 --> 00:58:22.884
Go home.

675
00:58:23.083 --> 00:58:27.480
And don't come back.
Or you're gonna get hurt.

676
00:58:40.235 --> 00:58:43.675
<i>Alice...
Things are...</i>

677
00:58:45.356 --> 00:58:48.113
<i>Things are bad again.</i>

678
00:58:48.831 --> 00:58:53.113
<i>Without Jake. I just...
I can't stand it.</i>

679
00:58:55.070 --> 00:58:57.551
<i>I don't see Edward anymore.</i>

680
00:58:58.912 --> 00:59:02.309
<i>Now it really feels like
he never existed.</i>

681
00:59:09.343 --> 00:59:12.986
<i>I will find a place
where I can see him again.</i>

682
01:00:07.727 --> 01:00:11.449
- Bella.
- Laurent.

683
01:00:12.767 --> 01:00:15.885
I didn't expect to find you here.

684
01:00:17.804 --> 01:00:22.841
I went to visit the Cullens. but...
their house is empty.

685
01:00:24.282 --> 01:00:26.882
I'm surprised they left you behind.

686
01:00:27.161 --> 01:00:29.079
Weren't you sort of a. um.

687
01:00:30.278 --> 01:00:32.319
...a pet of theirs?

688
01:00:32.718 --> 01:00:34.559
Yeah. You could say that.

689
01:00:34.600 --> 01:00:37.476
Do they Cullens visit often?

690
01:00:42.159 --> 01:00:43.677
<i>Lie.</i>

691
01:00:48.554 --> 01:00:51.232
Yeah. absolutely. all the time.
- Lie better.

692
01:00:51.593 --> 01:00:54.073
I'll tell them that you stopped by.

693
01:00:54.872 --> 01:00:58.109
I probably shouldn't tell...

694
01:00:59.388 --> 01:01:01.470
...Edward.

695
01:01:01.791 --> 01:01:06.467
Because he's pretty protective.
- But he's far away. isn't he?

696
01:01:08.347 --> 01:01:10.226
Why are you here?

697
01:01:10.268 --> 01:01:15.303
I came as a favor to Victoria.

698
01:01:17.583 --> 01:01:19.101
Victoria?

699
01:01:19.101 --> 01:01:22.982
She asked me to see if you were still
under the protection of the Cullens.

700
01:01:23.462 --> 01:01:27.098
Victoria feels it's only fair
to kill Edward's mate...

701
01:01:27.418 --> 01:01:29.019
...given he killed hers.

702
01:01:29.177 --> 01:01:31.218
An eye for an eye.

703
01:01:31.460 --> 01:01:34.416
Threaten him.
- Edward would know who did it!

704
01:01:34.656 --> 01:01:36.495
And he'd come after you.

705
01:01:37.256 --> 01:01:39.295
I don't think he will.

706
01:01:40.377 --> 01:01:43.213
After all. how much could
you mean to him...

707
01:01:43.853 --> 01:01:47.172
...if he left you here unprotected?

708
01:01:48.530 --> 01:01:51.732
Victoria won't be happy
about my killing you.

709
01:01:51.772 --> 01:01:54.254
But I can't help myself.

710
01:01:54.292 --> 01:01:57.250
You're so mouthwatering.
- Please. don't!

711
01:01:57.569 --> 01:01:59.209
I mean. you've helped us.
- Shhhh!

712
01:02:00.809 --> 01:02:04.367
Don't be afraid.
I'm doing you a kindness.

713
01:02:04.446 --> 01:02:10.124
Victoria plans on killing you
slowly. painfully.

714
01:02:10.645 --> 01:02:15.643
...where as I'll make it quick.
I promise.

715
01:02:17.222 --> 01:02:19.382
You will feel nothing.

716
01:02:24.787 --> 01:02:26.682
Edward. I love you.

717
01:02:28.045 --> 01:02:30.486
I don't believe it.

718
01:03:36.517 --> 01:03:38.516
Dad. I saw them!

719
01:03:38.596 --> 01:03:41.598
What's the matter?
- In the woods. They are not bears!

720
01:03:41.638 --> 01:03:44.314
What you mean in the woods? Bells. what
the hell were you doing out in the woods?

721
01:03:44.314 --> 01:03:48.196
They are wolves.
I mean. they're like huge wolves!

722
01:03:48.236 --> 01:03:51.316
Are you sure about that. Bella?
- Yeah. I just saw them.

723
01:03:51.356 --> 01:03:54.036
They were after... something.

724
01:03:54.235 --> 01:03:58.153
Wolves? You saw 'em?

725
01:04:00.873 --> 01:04:05.911
Alright. Well. Harry.
feel like going hunting?

726
01:04:05.911 --> 01:04:07.712
Get some of your guys together?

727
01:04:08.432 --> 01:04:11.512
Sure. yeah. I'll...
I'll just...

728
01:04:12.432 --> 01:04:14.751
<i>I know that those wolves
will be dead.</i>

729
01:04:15.751 --> 01:04:18.154
<i>And Laurent would have told her
I'm unprotected.</i>

730
01:04:18.955 --> 01:04:20.632
<i>Victoria.</i>

731
01:04:21.872 --> 01:04:23.672
I should go to the station.

732
01:04:23.713 --> 01:04:26.191
Dad. you should...
You should go.

733
01:04:26.392 --> 01:04:29.071
You can just stay in the house?

734
01:04:53.948 --> 01:04:55.747
Bella!

735
01:04:57.666 --> 01:04:59.187
Oh. you scared me.

736
01:04:59.187 --> 01:05:02.387
What the hell are you doing?
- Back up. I'm coming up.

737
01:05:14.880 --> 01:05:15.921
Hey.

738
01:05:18.425 --> 01:05:20.942
Look. look. I'm sorry.

739
01:05:26.941 --> 01:05:29.464
For what?
- I wish I could explain.

740
01:05:29.503 --> 01:05:33.102
...but I literally... can't!

741
01:05:41.500 --> 01:05:44.820
Have you ever had a secret
you couldn't tell anyone?

742
01:05:45.621 --> 01:05:48.060
One that wasn't yours to share.

743
01:05:51.220 --> 01:05:55.419
Well. that's what
it's like for me. Or worse.

744
01:05:56.539 --> 01:06:00.939
You have no idea.
how tight I'm bound.

745
01:06:01.099 --> 01:06:02.739
I hate this.

746
01:06:03.500 --> 01:06:05.538
I hate what they have
done to you.

747
01:06:19.857 --> 01:06:22.537
I mean. the killer part is
you already know!

748
01:06:27.095 --> 01:06:32.294
Bella. do you remember.
when walked on the beach in La Push?

749
01:06:33.335 --> 01:06:35.775
The sto...

750
01:06:38.613 --> 01:06:43.495
The story...
The story about the cold ones.

751
01:06:45.813 --> 01:06:49.893
I guees. I understand why that's
the only part you remember.

752
01:06:56.813 --> 01:07:00.650
There must gotta be something
You can do...

753
01:07:00.650 --> 01:07:03.252
No.
I'm in it for life.

754
01:07:04.131 --> 01:07:06.169
May be we should just
get out of here for a while.

755
01:07:06.728 --> 01:07:10.410
We'll just leave.
Just you and me.

756
01:07:10.849 --> 01:07:12.891
You can do that?

757
01:07:15.369 --> 01:07:17.570
I'll do it for you.

758
01:07:23.728 --> 01:07:27.469
It's not something
I can just run away from. Bella.

759
01:07:28.088 --> 01:07:33.048
But I would run away with you.

760
01:07:35.684 --> 01:07:38.486
If I could.

761
01:07:41.327 --> 01:07:45.564
I gotta go.
They'll certainly wonder where I am.

762
01:07:48.846 --> 01:07:50.362
Come here.

763
01:07:54.726 --> 01:07:58.765
Please...
Try to remember.

764
01:08:00.285 --> 01:08:05.402
It would be so much easier
if you knew...

765
01:08:07.884 --> 01:08:10.684
I'll try. but...
Jake.

766
01:08:11.004 --> 01:08:13.762
Jake. what are you doing?
Wait. Jake.

767
01:08:20.840 --> 01:08:22.360
Jake.

768
01:08:38.960 --> 01:08:40.758
Edward. I'm scared.

769
01:08:41.277 --> 01:08:43.317
You should be.

770
01:08:47.595 --> 01:08:50.275
<i>Really it's just like an old story...</i>

771
01:08:50.275 --> 01:08:51.956
<i>That we're not supposed to
say anything about...</i>

772
01:08:51.956 --> 01:08:55.714
<i>Did you know. the Quileute are
supposed to be descendants from wolves?</i>

773
01:09:10.435 --> 01:09:11.915
Bella.

774
01:09:11.954 --> 01:09:13.477
I need to see him.

775
01:09:14.595 --> 01:09:16.394
He's not in.

776
01:09:17.874 --> 01:09:20.373
I'm sorry. I really need to see him.
- Bella?

777
01:09:36.993 --> 01:09:38.710
What did you do?

778
01:09:38.711 --> 01:09:39.753
Okay. what did you do?

779
01:09:39.991 --> 01:09:42.231
Hey! What did you do to him?
- Easy!

780
01:09:42.231 --> 01:09:44.231
He didn't want this!
- What did we do?

781
01:09:44.231 --> 01:09:46.630
What did he do? What did he tell you?
- Both of you calm...

782
01:09:46.630 --> 01:09:49.871
Nothing! He told me nothing.
because he's scared of you!

783
01:09:55.627 --> 01:09:58.350
Too late. now.
- Bella. get back.

784
01:09:58.671 --> 01:10:01.746
Paul. calm down now.

785
01:10:10.027 --> 01:10:11.585
Bella!

786
01:10:12.505 --> 01:10:14.425
Run!

787
01:10:16.625 --> 01:10:18.349
Jake. run!

788
01:10:56.951 --> 01:10:59.428
Take Bella back to Emily's place.

789
01:11:00.308 --> 01:11:02.688
Guess the wolf's out of the bag.

790
01:11:07.667 --> 01:11:12.026
<i>Alice. is it possible that everything is true?</i>

791
01:11:12.066 --> 01:11:14.264
<i>Fairy tales and
horror stories?</i>

792
01:11:14.665 --> 01:11:18.667
<i>Is it possible that there isn't anything
sane and normal at all?</i>

793
01:11:20.305 --> 01:11:22.423
Hey. I think. we should go back
and see if Jacob's okay..

794
01:11:22.463 --> 01:11:25.024
I hope Paul sink some teeth into him.
Serves him right.

795
01:11:25.187 --> 01:11:28.222
No way. Jake's a natural.
You see him phase on the fly?

796
01:11:28.261 --> 01:11:30.264
I gott a five that says.
Paul doesn't touch him.

797
01:11:30.867 --> 01:11:32.985
Come on in. Bella.
We won't bite.

798
01:11:33.305 --> 01:11:34.865
Speak for yourself.

799
01:11:45.343 --> 01:11:47.864
Oh. hey. about Emily...
Sam's fiance.

800
01:11:47.864 --> 01:11:50.359
...don't stare.
It bugs Sam.

801
01:11:52.181 --> 01:11:54.062
Why would I stare?

802
01:11:54.101 --> 01:11:57.898
You guys hungry?
Like I have to ask...

803
01:12:04.540 --> 01:12:06.019
Who's this?

804
01:12:06.139 --> 01:12:08.500
Bella Swan.
Who else?

805
01:12:10.697 --> 01:12:13.618
So. youre the vampire girl.

806
01:12:16.019 --> 01:12:18.857
So. you're the wolf girl.

807
01:12:21.017 --> 01:12:22.538
Guess so.

808
01:12:22.538 --> 01:12:25.897
Well. I'm engaged to one.

809
01:12:27.977 --> 01:12:30.459
Save some for your brothers.

810
01:12:30.498 --> 01:12:32.414
And the ladies first.

811
01:12:32.455 --> 01:12:35.776
Muffin?
- Sure. Thanks.

812
01:12:35.815 --> 01:12:39.294
Leave it up to Jacob to find
a way around Sam's gag order.

813
01:12:39.334 --> 01:12:43.055
He didn't say anything to me.
- That's a wolf thing.

814
01:12:43.097 --> 01:12:45.618
Alpha's orders get obeyed
whether we want to or not.

815
01:12:45.618 --> 01:12:48.135
Oh. and check it out!
We can hear each other's thoughts.

816
01:12:48.135 --> 01:12:51.217
Will you just shut up?
These are trade secrets.

817
01:12:51.217 --> 01:12:54.654
Damn it!
This chick runs with vampires.

818
01:12:54.972 --> 01:12:57.494
Can't really run with vampires.

819
01:12:59.575 --> 01:13:01.611
Because they're fast.

820
01:13:01.652 --> 01:13:05.732
Yeah? Oh. we are faster.

821
01:13:05.973 --> 01:13:07.893
Freaked out yet?

822
01:13:09.052 --> 01:13:12.331
You're not the first monsters I've met.

823
01:13:12.370 --> 01:13:15.691
Jake's right.
You're good with weird.

824
01:13:37.247 --> 01:13:39.127
Sorry.

825
01:13:52.804 --> 01:13:55.207
So you're a werewolf?

826
01:13:56.567 --> 01:13:59.966
Yeah. last time I checked.

827
01:14:00.965 --> 01:14:04.246
A few lucky members of the
tribe have the gene.

828
01:14:04.567 --> 01:14:09.444
If a bloodsucker moves into town.
then the fever sets in.

829
01:14:11.484 --> 01:14:12.964
Mono?

830
01:14:13.843 --> 01:14:16.242
Yeah. I wish.

831
01:14:18.524 --> 01:14:23.360
Well. can't you find a way to stop?

832
01:14:24.963 --> 01:14:28.281
I mean it's wrong.

833
01:14:29.881 --> 01:14:32.441
It's not a life-style choice. Bella.

834
01:14:32.680 --> 01:14:35.260
I was born this way.
I can't help it.

835
01:14:35.353 --> 01:14:36.830
You are such a hypocrite.

836
01:14:36.830 --> 01:14:38.910
What. I'm not the
right kind of monster for you?

837
01:14:38.949 --> 01:14:43.144
It's not what you are.
It's what you do.

838
01:14:43.184 --> 01:14:45.183
They never hurt anybody.

839
01:14:46.262 --> 01:14:48.620
You killed people. Jake.

840
01:14:48.659 --> 01:14:51.575
Bella. we're not killing anyone.

841
01:14:52.694 --> 01:14:54.494
Then. who is?

842
01:14:54.494 --> 01:14:57.011
We're trying to protect
you people from them.

843
01:14:57.050 --> 01:14:59.967
The only thing we do kill.

844
01:15:01.725 --> 01:15:03.764
Vampiers.

845
01:15:04.561 --> 01:15:06.440
Jake. you can't...
- Don't worry.

846
01:15:06.440 --> 01:15:08.480
...we can't touch your little
precious Cullens.

847
01:15:08.480 --> 01:15:10.838
Unless they violate the Treaty.

848
01:15:11.436 --> 01:15:12.956
It's not what I'm saying.

849
01:15:13.395 --> 01:15:16.591
You can't kill vampires. though.

850
01:15:16.631 --> 01:15:20.307
They will kill you.
- Really? We took out

851
01:15:20.307 --> 01:15:22.466
...that leech with the dreads easy enough.

852
01:15:26.259 --> 01:15:27.738
Laurent?

853
01:15:27.738 --> 01:15:30.177
And his redhead girlfriend is next.

854
01:15:30.177 --> 01:15:32.895
Vic... Victoria is here?
- Was.

855
01:15:32.895 --> 01:15:35.572
We chased her all the way to the
Canadian border the other night.

856
01:15:35.572 --> 01:15:37.091
But she keeps coming back.

857
01:15:37.131 --> 01:15:40.247
We don't know what she's after.
- I do.

858
01:15:42.925 --> 01:15:45.403
Me.

859
01:15:53.634 --> 01:15:56.911
Don't worry.
we've got this place covered.

860
01:15:56.950 --> 01:15:59.429
She wont get near you or Charlie.

861
01:16:00.026 --> 01:16:02.103
But you gotta be careful.

862
01:16:02.103 --> 01:16:05.503
She's fast. you don't know.
how fast she is.

863
01:16:05.503 --> 01:16:08.620
You know. your lack of confidence
in us is a little insulting.

864
01:16:10.536 --> 01:16:13.094
Alright. I better go.

865
01:16:13.454 --> 01:16:17.487
And you gotta go.
- Yeah.

866
01:16:18.126 --> 01:16:20.526
I got a vampire to kill.

867
01:16:34.230 --> 01:16:37.310
<i>Alice. I'm alright.</i>

868
01:16:38.186 --> 01:16:40.225
<i>Until I'm alone.</i>

869
01:16:41.264 --> 01:16:43.982
<i>And lately.
that's all the time.</i>

870
01:16:43.982 --> 01:16:46.978
<i>Jacob's gone.
he's hunting for Victoria.</i>

871
01:16:46.978 --> 01:16:49.335
<i>And Charlie is hunting Jacob.</i>

872
01:16:49.375 --> 01:16:50.894
<i>And you're gone.</i>

873
01:16:51.893 --> 01:16:54.370
<i>And so is Edward.</i>

874
01:16:57.290 --> 01:16:59.883
<i>And I just have nothing now.</i>

875
01:17:03.083 --> 01:17:04.641
You got something. Harry?

876
01:17:05.401 --> 01:17:08.476
Nope. nothing.

877
01:17:15.147 --> 01:17:17.547
<i>But I realize where I have to go.</i>

878
01:17:17.547 --> 01:17:19.705
<i>What I have to do
to see him again.</i>

879
01:20:17.563 --> 01:20:19.602
<i>Don't do this.</i>

880
01:20:23.997 --> 01:20:26.396
You wanted me to be human.

881
01:20:27.915 --> 01:20:30.790
Watch me.

882
01:20:32.549 --> 01:20:36.506
<i>Please? For me?</i>

883
01:20:36.506 --> 01:20:38.661
You won't stay with me
any other way.

884
01:20:41.422 --> 01:20:44.176
<i>Bella. Please.</i>

885
01:22:25.297 --> 01:22:27.014
Breathe.

886
01:22:27.735 --> 01:22:30.691
Come on. Bella.
Breathe.

887
01:22:36.765 --> 01:22:40.561
Bella?
Bella. can you hear me?

888
01:22:45.995 --> 01:22:47.633
Jake.

889
01:22:55.864 --> 01:23:01.260
What the hell were you thinking. huh?
- I just needed to see something.

890
01:23:01.977 --> 01:23:05.776
Take her home.
I'm gonna go help over at Harry's place.

891
01:23:08.414 --> 01:23:10.730
What happened at Harry's?

892
01:23:10.730 --> 01:23:13.208
Harry Clearwater
had a heart attack.

893
01:23:13.327 --> 01:23:16.881
Charlie and my Dad are at Harry's place
with his family.

894
01:23:16.881 --> 01:23:21.998
Is he okay?
- He's gone.

895
01:23:25.234 --> 01:23:29.351
Come on. I'll give you something dry
and drive you home.

896
01:23:39.382 --> 01:23:42.859
Hundred and eight degrees over here.

897
01:23:44.696 --> 01:23:49.133
God! My hands are freezing.

898
01:23:51.010 --> 01:23:53.486
It must be nice. never getting cold.

899
01:23:53.525 --> 01:23:57.963
Its a wolf thing.
- It's not.

900
01:23:57.963 --> 01:24:02.396
Its a Jacob thing.
Youre just warm.

901
01:24:04.755 --> 01:24:07.431
You're like. your own sun.

902
01:24:10.428 --> 01:24:14.863
This is better.
Now that you know about me.

903
01:24:17.662 --> 01:24:19.620
But...?

904
01:24:24.094 --> 01:24:26.892
You saw what happened to Emily.

905
01:24:29.928 --> 01:24:34.644
Sam got angry. lost it for a split second...

906
01:24:35.643 --> 01:24:38.559
...Em was standing too close.

907
01:24:40.237 --> 01:24:43.193
He will never be able
to take that back.

908
01:24:45.391 --> 01:24:48.072
What if I get mad at you?

909
01:24:59.179 --> 01:25:01.697
Sometimes...

910
01:25:03.018 --> 01:25:06.132
I feel like. I'm gonna disappear.

911
01:25:12.165 --> 01:25:17.961
You know you don't need me.
to tell you something like this.

912
01:25:19.240 --> 01:25:23.634
But I always will.
You're not gonna loose yourself.

913
01:25:25.632 --> 01:25:28.109
I won't let that happen.

914
01:25:30.231 --> 01:25:32.106
How?

915
01:25:34.662 --> 01:25:37.900
I'll tell you all the time.

916
01:25:39.819 --> 01:25:43.893
How special you are.

917
01:26:01.916 --> 01:26:06.230
Thank you...
...for everything.

918
01:26:11.505 --> 01:26:13.062
Wait!

919
01:26:15.384 --> 01:26:18.657
There's a vampire.
- How do you know?

920
01:26:19.299 --> 01:26:22.374
I can smell it.
I'm getting you out.

921
01:26:23.453 --> 01:26:27.927
That's Carlisle's car!
Theyre here.

922
01:26:28.528 --> 01:26:32.124
Bella. it's a trick. Stop!
You gotta come with me.

923
01:26:35.322 --> 01:26:36.798
They won't hurt me.

924
01:26:36.961 --> 01:26:40.396
If a Cullen is back here.
this is their territory.

925
01:26:40.396 --> 01:26:43.553
The treaty says we can only
defend in our own lands.

926
01:26:43.553 --> 01:26:47.669
I can't protect you here.
- Okay. it's okay. You don't have to.

927
01:26:49.788 --> 01:26:51.825
Youre about to cross a line.

928
01:26:51.825 --> 01:26:55.459
Then don't draw one. Please?

929
01:27:12.084 --> 01:27:14.562
Alice?!
Oh my God!

930
01:27:14.562 --> 01:27:16.040
Bella?
- What are you...?

931
01:27:16.838 --> 01:27:20.196
I'm sorry. I just...
I can't believe you're here. Is...is..

932
01:27:21.195 --> 01:27:24.392
Would you like to explain to me
how you're alive?

933
01:27:25.029 --> 01:27:28.108
What?
- I saw a vision of you.

934
01:27:28.227 --> 01:27:32.661
You jumped off a cliff. Why in the hell
would you try and kill yourself?

935
01:27:32.661 --> 01:27:36.020
I mean. what about Charlie? What about...?
- I didn't try to kill myself.

936
01:27:36.380 --> 01:27:39.615
I was cliff jumping.
Recreationally!

937
01:27:39.775 --> 01:27:42.612
It was fun.

938
01:27:43.491 --> 01:27:49.045
I have never met anyone more prone
to life-threatening idiocy.

939
01:27:54.840 --> 01:27:58.116
Did you... did you tell him?
- No.

940
01:27:59.555 --> 01:28:03.591
He only calls once in a few months.

941
01:28:04.070 --> 01:28:06.626
He said he wants to be alone.

942
01:28:12.342 --> 01:28:16.897
Bella. what is that
God awful wet dog smell?

943
01:28:18.376 --> 01:28:21.411
That's probably me

944
01:28:23.170 --> 01:28:26.530
Or... it's Jacob.
- Jacob who?

945
01:28:27.647 --> 01:28:34.539
Jacob's kind of a werewolf. Ugh! Bella!
Werewolves are not good company to keep!

946
01:28:35.939 --> 01:28:38.256
Speak for yourself.

947
01:28:42.632 --> 01:28:45.348
I had to see if you were safe.

948
01:28:46.069 --> 01:28:48.845
I thought you couldn't protect me here.

949
01:28:49.223 --> 01:28:51.121
Guess. I don't care.

950
01:28:54.700 --> 01:28:56.997
Well. I'm not gonna hurt her.

951
01:28:58.456 --> 01:29:00.693
No. you're just a harmless Cullen.

952
01:29:00.694 --> 01:29:03.131
We're talking about the other
bloodsucker who tried to kill Bella

953
01:29:03.131 --> 01:29:05.208
...because of you.
- Victoria?

954
01:29:05.208 --> 01:29:07.448
Yeah. Victoria has been around.

955
01:29:07.448 --> 01:29:12.719
I didn't see her. I didn't see you
get pulled out of the water either.

956
01:29:14.318 --> 01:29:17.397
I can't see past you
and your pack of mutts!

957
01:29:17.397 --> 01:29:20.273
Don't get me upset.
- Hey. stop!

958
01:29:20.273 --> 01:29:23.509
Things are gonna get very ugly!
- Stop! Stop! Stop!

959
01:29:29.183 --> 01:29:31.423
I will give you a minute.

960
01:29:39.016 --> 01:29:42.412
You're going anywhere.
you're gonna come back. right?

961
01:29:42.412 --> 01:29:45.169
As soon as you put the dog out.

962
01:29:52.682 --> 01:29:55.796
Is he...?

963
01:29:58.954 --> 01:30:02.949
Are there others? How many Cullens are here
and how long are they staying?

964
01:30:04.586 --> 01:30:07.146
No. It's just Alice.

965
01:30:11.102 --> 01:30:14.259
And she can stay
as long as she like.

966
01:30:15.896 --> 01:30:18.453
Are the rest coming back?

967
01:30:24.846 --> 01:30:26.605
No.

968
01:30:27.606 --> 01:30:30.241
Not that I know of.

969
01:30:30.561 --> 01:30:32.357
Anything else?

970
01:30:35.917 --> 01:30:37.933
That's it.

971
01:30:39.990 --> 01:30:43.686
Well. if that's all. then you better go
run back to Sam.

972
01:30:46.506 --> 01:30:49.223
I have done it again.

973
01:30:49.624 --> 01:30:52.859
I keep breaking my promise.

974
01:30:56.657 --> 01:30:59.570
We don't have to do this to each other.

975
01:31:03.728 --> 01:31:06.445
Yes. we do.

976
01:31:17.355 --> 01:31:18.872
Bella...

977
01:31:23.036 --> 01:31:26.204
"Que Quowle"
(Stay with me. forever)

978
01:31:41.411 --> 01:31:43.686
Swan Residence.

979
01:31:48.604 --> 01:31:54.256
He's not here right now.
He's arranging a funeral.

980
01:32:08.823 --> 01:32:14.736
Who is that? What?
- Always in the way.

981
01:32:16.416 --> 01:32:19.650
Who was that?
- Bella. step back.

982
01:32:19.650 --> 01:32:21.290
Jake. who was that?
- Stop.

983
01:32:21.530 --> 01:32:24.327
Bella. it's Edward.
He thinks you are dead.

984
01:32:24.487 --> 01:32:27.723
Rosalie told him.
why I came here.

985
01:32:28.721 --> 01:32:31.720
Why didn't you let me speak to him?

986
01:32:31.720 --> 01:32:34.075
He didn't ask for you.
- I don't care!

987
01:32:34.075 --> 01:32:36.675
Bella. he's going to the Volturi.

988
01:32:37.114 --> 01:32:39.511
He wants to die too.

989
01:32:41.588 --> 01:32:44.387
He left you. Bella.
He didn't want you anymore. remember?

990
01:32:44.387 --> 01:32:48.041
But I'm not gonna let him
kill himself out of guilt.

991
01:32:48.661 --> 01:32:52.137
What about your Dad?
- I'm eighteen.

992
01:32:52.137 --> 01:32:54.854
I'm legally free to go.
And I left a note.

993
01:32:56.292 --> 01:33:02.127
Please. Bella.
Just... stay here.

994
01:33:03.086 --> 01:33:05.363
Not for Charlie.

995
01:33:06.962 --> 01:33:09.360
For me...

996
01:33:09.558 --> 01:33:12.436
I have to go.

997
01:33:16.834 --> 01:33:19.471
I'm begging you.

998
01:33:21.309 --> 01:33:23.785
Please.

999
01:33:24.944 --> 01:33:27.343
Goodbye. Jacob.

1000
01:33:35.054 --> 01:33:36.654
Okay.

1001
01:34:36.911 --> 01:34:40.029
So you made up your minds?

1002
01:34:40.150 --> 01:34:43.108
I'm afraid your particular gifts...

1003
01:34:43.865 --> 01:34:46.664
...are too valuable
to destroy.

1004
01:34:46.783 --> 01:34:50.258
But if you're unhappy
with your lot.

1005
01:34:50.776 --> 01:34:52.736
...join us.

1006
01:34:52.975 --> 01:34:56.971
We would be delighted
to utilize your skills.

1007
01:34:57.173 --> 01:35:00.288
Won't you consider
staying with us?

1008
01:35:01.486 --> 01:35:04.085
You know what will happen anyway.

1009
01:35:04.286 --> 01:35:07.200
Not without cause.

1010
01:35:10.119 --> 01:35:12.995
Such a waste.

1011
01:35:18.790 --> 01:35:20.866
I'm guessing you didn't rent this car?

1012
01:35:20.866 --> 01:35:23.104
I figured. you wouldn't be
opposed to grand theft auto.

1013
01:35:23.104 --> 01:35:24.624
Not today.

1014
01:35:27.420 --> 01:35:31.016
What? What are you seeing?
- They refused him.

1015
01:35:31.016 --> 01:35:34.172
So...?
- He's gonna make a scene.

1016
01:35:34.172 --> 01:35:36.250
Show himself to the humans.
- No! When?

1017
01:35:37.970 --> 01:35:41.286
He's gonna wait until noon.
when the sun's at it's highest.

1018
01:35:43.564 --> 01:35:46.641
Alice. you gotta hurry up.
- There's Volterra.

1019
01:36:11.693 --> 01:36:14.733
Why are they all in red?
- Saint Marcos Day festival.

1020
01:36:14.733 --> 01:36:17.330
They're commemorating the expulsion
of vampires from the city.

1021
01:36:17.529 --> 01:36:19.087
It's the perfect setting.

1022
01:36:19.087 --> 01:36:21.685
The Volturi will never let him
get far enough to reveal himself

1023
01:36:21.685 --> 01:36:26.440
We have 5 minutes.
- I know. Bella? Just breathe.

1024
01:36:31.123 --> 01:36:32.162
Alice!?

1025
01:36:32.753 --> 01:36:35.150
Bella. you're the only one
he can't see coming.

1026
01:36:35.270 --> 01:36:38.390
If I go. he will read my thoughts.
he'll think I'm lying and rush into it.

1027
01:36:38.988 --> 01:36:42.384
Where do I go?
- He'll be under the clock tower. Go!

1028
01:38:34.550 --> 01:38:36.308
No!

1029
01:38:37.626 --> 01:38:39.146
Heaven.

1030
01:38:39.185 --> 01:38:40.665
You have to move!

1031
01:38:41.584 --> 01:38:44.580
Open your eyes. look at me.
I'm alive.

1032
01:38:44.979 --> 01:38:46.979
You have to move!

1033
01:38:47.498 --> 01:38:49.015
Bella?

1034
01:38:56.288 --> 01:38:59.303
You're here.
- Yeah.

1035
01:39:01.204 --> 01:39:03.064
You're alive!

1036
01:39:05.876 --> 01:39:07.434
Yes.

1037
01:39:16.258 --> 01:39:19.032
I needed to make you see me once.

1038
01:39:20.213 --> 01:39:23.968
You had to know that I was alive.
You didn't have to feel guilty or anything.

1039
01:39:27.482 --> 01:39:31.241
I can let you go now.

1040
01:39:34.873 --> 01:39:37.470
Never like that again.

1041
01:39:38.990 --> 01:39:42.504
I just couldn't live in a world
where you don't exist.

1042
01:39:44.222 --> 01:39:46.939
But you said...
- I lied.

1043
01:39:47.219 --> 01:39:50.733
I had to lie
and you believe me so easily

1044
01:39:55.408 --> 01:39:59.485
Because it doesn't make sense
for you to love me.

1045
01:40:01.959 --> 01:40:05.875
I'm nothing... human.
Nothing.

1046
01:40:06.795 --> 01:40:11.147
Bella. you're everything to me.

1047
01:40:12.227 --> 01:40:14.187
Everything.

1048
01:40:39.594 --> 01:40:41.911
I won't be needing your services
after all. gentlemen.

1049
01:40:41.911 --> 01:40:43.950
Aro wants to speak with you again.

1050
01:40:43.990 --> 01:40:46.145
No rules were broken.
- Nonetheless. we should take this

1051
01:40:46.145 --> 01:40:49.502
...conversation to a more
appropriate venue.

1052
01:40:49.582 --> 01:40:51.578
Fine.

1053
01:40:51.981 --> 01:40:54.573
Bella. why don't you go enjoy
the rest of the festival?

1054
01:40:54.654 --> 01:40:57.931
The girl comes with us.
- No. You can go to hell.

1055
01:41:00.090 --> 01:41:03.285
Come on. guys.
It's a festival.

1056
01:41:03.405 --> 01:41:05.723
We wouldn't want to make a scene.

1057
01:41:06.082 --> 01:41:07.918
We wouldnt.

1058
01:41:07.957 --> 01:41:09.518
Enough!

1059
01:41:10.837 --> 01:41:12.354
Jane.

1060
01:41:12.554 --> 01:41:15.350
Aro send me to see
what's taking so long.

1061
01:41:23.780 --> 01:41:25.978
Just do as she says.

1062
01:41:38.238 --> 01:41:39.982
Go ahead.

1063
01:41:43.755 --> 01:41:45.814
Are you scared?

1064
01:41:46.393 --> 01:41:48.171
Are you?

1065
01:41:48.549 --> 01:41:50.168
No.

1066
01:41:50.169 --> 01:41:51.209
Hmmh.

1067
01:42:21.867 --> 01:42:23.765
"Buon pomeriggio!"
(Good afternoon!)

1068
01:42:28.139 --> 01:42:30.658
Is she human?
- Yes.

1069
01:42:33.534 --> 01:42:36.649
Does she know?
- Yes.

1070
01:42:37.048 --> 01:42:39.027
Then why would...

1071
01:42:40.487 --> 01:42:42.482
She wants to be...

1072
01:42:42.683 --> 01:42:45.798
And so she will be.
- Or dessert!

1073
01:42:54.229 --> 01:42:58.343
Sister. sent you out to get one
and you bring back two.

1074
01:42:58.784 --> 01:43:00.662
And a half.

1075
01:43:01.420 --> 01:43:02.537
Such a clever girl.

1076
01:43:02.937 --> 01:43:05.255
What a happy surprise!

1077
01:43:05.693 --> 01:43:09.092
Bella is alive after all.

1078
01:43:09.332 --> 01:43:12.764
Isn't that wonderful?

1079
01:43:12.964 --> 01:43:15.322
I love a happy ending.

1080
01:43:19.276 --> 01:43:21.475
They are so rare.

1081
01:43:25.190 --> 01:43:27.906
"La Tua Cantante"
(Your Singer)

1082
01:43:27.945 --> 01:43:30.744
Your blood appeals to you
so much...

1083
01:43:31.741 --> 01:43:33.817
...it makes me thirsty.

1084
01:43:33.858 --> 01:43:36.737
How can you stand
to be so close to her?

1085
01:43:36.817 --> 01:43:40.511
It's not without difficulty.
- Yes. I can see that.

1086
01:43:43.207 --> 01:43:45.685
Aro can read every thought
I ever had.

1087
01:43:45.764 --> 01:43:47.400
With one touch.

1088
01:43:48.002 --> 01:43:49.839
And now you know everything.

1089
01:43:50.798 --> 01:43:52.437
So. get on with it.

1090
01:43:55.311 --> 01:43:59.546
You're quite a soul reader
yourself. Edward.

1091
01:44:00.267 --> 01:44:05.181
Though you can't read Bella's thoughts.

1092
01:44:07.779 --> 01:44:09.577
Fascinating!

1093
01:44:13.213 --> 01:44:19.045
I would love to see if you are an
exception to my gifts. as well.

1094
01:44:21.044 --> 01:44:23.078
Would you do me the honor?

1095
01:44:43.973 --> 01:44:45.771
Interesting.

1096
01:44:47.652 --> 01:44:49.567
I see nothing.

1097
01:45:01.028 --> 01:45:02.669
I wonder if...

1098
01:45:03.108 --> 01:45:06.781
Let's see if she is immune
to all our powers.

1099
01:45:07.741 --> 01:45:09.419
Shall we. Jane?

1100
01:45:11.295 --> 01:45:13.532
No!
- Pain.

1101
01:45:31.154 --> 01:45:32.832
Stop!
Don't. Please stop!

1102
01:45:33.670 --> 01:45:37.146
Stop! Stop hurting him!
Please. please!

1103
01:45:38.345 --> 01:45:40.022
Jane?

1104
01:45:41.620 --> 01:45:43.337
Master?

1105
01:45:47.213 --> 01:45:49.250
Go ahead. my dear.

1106
01:45:54.484 --> 01:45:56.439
This may hurt just a little.

1107
01:46:12.859 --> 01:46:15.097
Remarkable!

1108
01:46:16.457 --> 01:46:19.572
She confounds us all.

1109
01:46:19.773 --> 01:46:23.687
So. what we do with you now?

1110
01:46:23.727 --> 01:46:27.162
You already know
what you're going to do. Aro.

1111
01:46:27.521 --> 01:46:31.878
She knows too much.
she's a liability.

1112
01:46:35.872 --> 01:46:37.471
That's true.

1113
01:46:41.183 --> 01:46:42.862
Felix.

1114
01:47:48.824 --> 01:47:52.217
Please! No. no!
Please! Please!

1115
01:47:54.854 --> 01:47:58.454
Kill me... kill me.
Not him.

1116
01:48:08.996 --> 01:48:12.274
How extraordinary.

1117
01:48:13.192 --> 01:48:18.547
You would give up your life
for someone like us.

1118
01:48:18.746 --> 01:48:20.345
A vampire.

1119
01:48:21.500 --> 01:48:24.377
A soulless monster.

1120
01:48:24.378 --> 01:48:26.463
Just get away from him!

1121
01:48:30.011 --> 01:48:35.164
You don't know a thing about his soul.

1122
01:48:37.247 --> 01:48:44.441
"Forse nè del vostro l'uno l'altro"
(Maybe yours is one or the other)

1123
01:48:45.870 --> 01:48:48.268
This is a sadness.

1124
01:48:49.867 --> 01:48:53.943
If only it be your intention
to give her immortality.

1125
01:49:02.413 --> 01:49:03.971
Wait!

1126
01:49:05.247 --> 01:49:07.404
Bella will be one of us.

1127
01:49:08.925 --> 01:49:10.442
I've seen it.

1128
01:49:12.317 --> 01:49:14.277
I'll change her myself.

1129
01:49:47.991 --> 01:49:49.671
Mesmerizing!

1130
01:49:49.790 --> 01:49:55.305
To see. what you have seen.
Before it is happened.

1131
01:49:57.421 --> 01:50:02.972
Your gifts will make for
an intriguing

1132
01:50:03.052 --> 01:50:05.252
...immortal.

1133
01:50:05.332 --> 01:50:08.370
Isabella.

1134
01:50:11.964 --> 01:50:16.400
Go now.
Make your preparations.

1135
01:50:16.680 --> 01:50:19.515
Let us be done with this.

1136
01:50:20.636 --> 01:50:23.751
Heidi will arrive. any moment.

1137
01:50:24.388 --> 01:50:29.744
Thank you for your visit.
- We'll return the favor.

1138
01:50:29.825 --> 01:50:35.217
I would advise that you follow through on your
promise soon. We do not offer second chances.

1139
01:50:36.815 --> 01:50:41.328
Goodbye. my young friends.

1140
01:50:46.162 --> 01:50:48.219
Nice fishing. Heidi.

1141
01:50:48.240 --> 01:50:50.438
Yes. they do look rather juicy.

1142
01:50:50.519 --> 01:50:52.597
Save some for me.

1143
01:50:53.193 --> 01:50:57.029
This way. please.
Stay together.

1144
01:51:11.605 --> 01:51:12.646
Stop! Stop!

1145
01:51:23.036 --> 01:51:25.117
You're here.

1146
01:51:26.754 --> 01:51:28.770
You can sleep.

1147
01:51:31.746 --> 01:51:35.065
I'll still be here
when you wake up.

1148
01:51:38.018 --> 01:51:42.135
Bella. the only reason
I left

1149
01:51:42.734 --> 01:51:46.247
...was because I thought
I was protecting you.

1150
01:51:47.767 --> 01:51:50.643
I needed you to have a chance...

1151
01:51:50.643 --> 01:51:54.439
...at a normal. happy life.

1152
01:51:57.315 --> 01:52:01.030
It was so easy for you to leave.

1153
01:52:02.310 --> 01:52:06.863
Leaving you was the hardest thing
I've done in a 100 years.

1154
01:52:12.653 --> 01:52:15.372
I swear...

1155
01:52:15.850 --> 01:52:19.768
I will never fail you again.

1156
01:52:20.685 --> 01:52:23.000
I'm so sorry.

1157
01:52:24.521 --> 01:52:26.559
Charlie's coming.
- Hey!

1158
01:52:29.752 --> 01:52:31.913
You okay?

1159
01:52:32.552 --> 01:52:34.389
Fine.

1160
01:52:36.588 --> 01:52:38.944
Dad. you don't have to worry.

1161
01:52:39.624 --> 01:52:43.977
Yeah. last time you said that you took off.
I didn't see you for three days.

1162
01:52:45.096 --> 01:52:47.894
I'm really sorry. Dad.

1163
01:52:49.131 --> 01:52:53.966
Bella. do not ever do that
to me again.

1164
01:52:55.724 --> 01:52:57.399
Ever.

1165
01:52:59.596 --> 01:53:01.555
And you're grounded...

1166
01:53:01.674 --> 01:53:04.870
...for the rest of your life.

1167
01:53:04.910 --> 01:53:06.710
Okay.

1168
01:53:16.498 --> 01:53:19.371
I'm not technically breaking
any of his rules.

1169
01:53:21.891 --> 01:53:25.086
He did say. I couldn't take a step
inside through the door.

1170
01:53:25.606 --> 01:53:28.121
I came in through the window.

1171
01:53:31.639 --> 01:53:34.714
He's not going to forgive me easily.

1172
01:53:36.673 --> 01:53:38.231
I know.

1173
01:53:39.867 --> 01:53:41.705
Can you?

1174
01:53:44.824 --> 01:53:47.300
I hope you can because...

1175
01:53:47.500 --> 01:53:51.336
I honestly don't know
how to live without you.

1176
01:53:54.569 --> 01:53:57.687
Come here.

1177
01:54:13.946 --> 01:54:18.102
Once Alice changes me.

1178
01:54:19.420 --> 01:54:22.217
...you can't get rid of me.

1179
01:54:23.095 --> 01:54:25.892
She won't need to change you.

1180
01:54:26.332 --> 01:54:29.326
There are always ways to keep
the Volturi in the dark.

1181
01:54:31.364 --> 01:54:34.521
No.

1182
01:54:40.471 --> 01:54:43.032
You all know what I want.

1183
01:54:44.549 --> 01:54:49.023
And I know.
how much I'm asking for.

1184
01:54:50.021 --> 01:54:53.577
The only thing I can think of...
for it to be fair is to just vote.

1185
01:54:53.657 --> 01:54:56.856
You don't know what you just...
- Shut up!

1186
01:54:58.335 --> 01:54:59.889
Alice?

1187
01:55:00.049 --> 01:55:02.687
I already consider you my sister.

1188
01:55:06.522 --> 01:55:08.119
'Yes'!
- Thank you.

1189
01:55:08.199 --> 01:55:10.437
I vote. 'yes'.

1190
01:55:10.918 --> 01:55:14.991
It would be nice to not wanna
kill you all the time.

1191
01:55:17.589 --> 01:55:19.746
I'm sorry.

1192
01:55:20.784 --> 01:55:24.619
I'm really sorry. both of you.
for the way I've acted.

1193
01:55:24.699 --> 01:55:29.013
And I'm really grateful that you were brave
enough to go and save my brother.

1194
01:55:30.411 --> 01:55:34.448
But this isn't a life
I would have chosen for myself.

1195
01:55:36.086 --> 01:55:39.721
And I wish that there had been
someone to vote 'no' for me.

1196
01:55:42.598 --> 01:55:45.313
So... 'no'.

1197
01:55:45.672 --> 01:55:48.110
I vote hell yeah!

1198
01:55:49.508 --> 01:55:52.023
We can pick a fight with
these Volturi's some other way.

1199
01:55:52.023 --> 01:55:54.544
I already consider you.
a part of the family.

1200
01:55:55.543 --> 01:55:57.657
'Yes'.

1201
01:56:02.492 --> 01:56:04.768
Why are you doing this to me?

1202
01:56:06.287 --> 01:56:09.925
You know what this means.
- You've chosen not to live without her.

1203
01:56:10.005 --> 01:56:12.003
...which leaves me no choice.

1204
01:56:12.482 --> 01:56:14.799
I won't lose my son.

1205
01:56:20.669 --> 01:56:23.229
<i>I'll wait until after graduation...</i>

1206
01:56:23.229 --> 01:56:26.183
<i>...to make it easier on Charlie.</i>

1207
01:56:29.538 --> 01:56:32.697
I want you to be the one
to do it.

1208
01:56:39.327 --> 01:56:41.685
He wants to talk to me.

1209
01:56:44.641 --> 01:56:46.360
See. you're still alive for now.

1210
01:56:46.400 --> 01:56:48.755
He thinks. it's me keeping you away.

1211
01:56:48.956 --> 01:56:51.233
You stay the hell out of my head.

1212
01:56:52.393 --> 01:56:56.866
Jacob. I know you have
something to say to me.

1213
01:56:58.225 --> 01:57:01.261
But I wanna say something to you first.
If that's alright?

1214
01:57:03.058 --> 01:57:05.214
Thank you.

1215
01:57:08.053 --> 01:57:11.888
Thank you for keeping
Bella alive when I didnt.

1216
01:57:11.888 --> 01:57:15.085
No. you didn't.

1217
01:57:15.603 --> 01:57:18.478
And it wasn't for your benefit.
trust me.

1218
01:57:18.598 --> 01:57:20.557
I'm still grateful.

1219
01:57:20.959 --> 01:57:22.437
But I'm here now.

1220
01:57:22.437 --> 01:57:25.110
And I'm not gonna leave her side
till she orders me away.

1221
01:57:25.191 --> 01:57:27.230
We'll see.

1222
01:57:30.625 --> 01:57:32.863
Hey. my turn to talk.

1223
01:57:36.059 --> 01:57:39.213
I'm here to remind you about
a key point in the Treaty.

1224
01:57:39.772 --> 01:57:41.652
I haven't forgotten.

1225
01:57:41.853 --> 01:57:43.371
What key point?

1226
01:57:43.449 --> 01:57:48.162
If any of them bites a human.
the truce is over.

1227
01:57:49.681 --> 01:57:51.719
But if I choose it.
it has nothing to do with you.

1228
01:57:51.839 --> 01:57:54.555
No... No. I won't let you.

1229
01:57:55.114 --> 01:57:57.590
You're not gonna be
one of them. Bella.

1230
01:57:57.711 --> 01:57:59.908
It's not up to you.

1231
01:58:00.347 --> 01:58:01.946
You know what we'll do to you.

1232
01:58:01.946 --> 01:58:04.544
I won't have choice.
- Bella. please come.

1233
01:58:04.624 --> 01:58:06.540
Wait.

1234
01:58:07.817 --> 01:58:10.376
Is he gonna hurt me?
Read his mind.

1235
01:58:17.406 --> 01:58:20.003
Jake...

1236
01:58:25.276 --> 01:58:28.593
I love you.

1237
01:58:31.628 --> 01:58:33.908
So. please...

1238
01:58:37.902 --> 01:58:40.739
Don't make me choose.

1239
01:58:45.769 --> 01:58:48.090
Because it'll be him.

1240
01:58:50.765 --> 01:58:53.603
It's always been him.

1241
01:59:00.890 --> 01:59:01.933
Bella.

1242
01:59:09.463 --> 01:59:12.458
Goodbye. Jacob.
- No. you don't speak for her!

1243
01:59:17.454 --> 01:59:19.490
Bella. get out of here.

1244
01:59:21.126 --> 01:59:23.726
Stop!

1245
01:59:24.444 --> 01:59:26.043
Stop!

1246
01:59:26.123 --> 01:59:29.037
You can't hurt each other
without hurting me.

1247
01:59:47.977 --> 01:59:49.734
Jake...

1248
02:00:04.115 --> 02:00:05.993
He's right.

1249
02:00:06.673 --> 02:00:09.552
You shouldn't become
what I am.

1250
02:00:13.864 --> 02:00:15.981
I can't do this alone.

1251
02:00:18.856 --> 02:00:21.214
Then please just wait.

1252
02:00:27.766 --> 02:00:31.124
Just give me... five years.

1253
02:00:35.915 --> 02:00:38.034
It's too long.

1254
02:00:41.748 --> 02:00:44.186
Then. three?

1255
02:00:48.142 --> 02:00:50.698
You're so stubborn.

1256
02:00:51.417 --> 02:00:54.371
What are you waiting for?

1257
02:01:02.244 --> 02:01:06.998
I have one condition...

1258
02:01:07.877 --> 02:01:11.632
...if you want me
to do it myself.

1259
02:01:14.270 --> 02:01:16.346
What's the condition?

1260
02:01:16.824 --> 02:01:19.383
And then. forever.

1261
02:01:20.383 --> 02:01:23.578
That's what I'm asking.

1262
02:01:33.485 --> 02:01:37.559
Marry me. Bella.
